{"title_page": "Gary Lucas", "text_new": "{{short description|American musician}}\n{{about|the musician|the baseball player|Gary Lucas (baseball)|the rapper|Joyner Lucas}}\n{{Primary sources|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name             = Gary Lucas\n| image            =\n| caption          = Gary Lucas at the London Tribute to Jeff Buckley on September 9, 2017<br />Photo by Michael Ark\n| background    = solo_singer\n| birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|1952|6|20}}\n| birth_place     = [[Syracuse, New York|Syracuse]], New York, United States\n| genre             = [[Rock music|Rock]], [[experimental rock]], pop, blues\n| occupation     = Musician, singer-songwriter, producer\n| instrument     = Guitar\n| years_active  = 1970s\u2013present\n| label              = [[Knitting Factory Records|Knitting Factory]], [[Tzadik Records|Tzadik]], [[Enemy Records|Enemy]], [[Northern Spy Records|Northern Spy]]\n| associated_acts = [[Captain Beefheart]], [[Gods and Monsters (band)|Gods and Monsters]], the Du-Tels, Chase the Devil\n| website           = {{URL|www.garylucas.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Gary Lucas''' (born June 20, 1952) is an American guitarist who was a member of [[Captain Beefheart]]'s band. He formed the band [[Gods and Monsters (band)|Gods and Monsters]] in 1989.\n\nLucas has collaborated with [[Leonard Bernstein]], [[Jeff Buckley]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jeffbuckley.com/jbin/13-08.html |title=The Jeff Buckley International Newsletter |website=Jeffbuckley.com |accessdate=2014-07-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929130026/http://www.jeffbuckley.com/jbin/13-08.html |archivedate=2013-09-29 }}</ref> [[John Cale]], [[Nick Cave]], [[David Johansen]], and [[Lou Reed]].\n\nHe has also worked with [[Chris Cornell]], [[The Dark Poets]], [[DJ Spooky]], [[Dr. John]], [[Amanda Palmer]], [[Bryan Ferry]], [[The Future Sound of London]], [[Allen Ginsberg]], [[Peter Hammill]], [[Warren Haynes]], [[Jann Klose]], [[Dave Liebman]], [[Joe Lovano]], [[Melissa Mars]], [[Kate & Anna McGarrigle]], [[Geoff Muldaur]], [[Bob Neuwirth]], [[Mary Margaret O'Hara]], [[Onetwo (band)|Onetwo]], [[Graham Parker]], [[Van Dyke Parks]], [[Iggy Pop]], [[Roswell Rudd]], [[Fred Schneider]], [[Richard Barone]], [[John Sebastian]], [[Adrian Sherwood]], [[Patti Smith]], [[Peter Stampfel]], [[Damo Suzuki]], [[Steve Swallow]], [[Matthew Sweet]], [[Bob Weir]], [[John Zorn]], [[Nona Hendryx]], [[Emir Kusturica]] and the [[No Smoking Orchestra]], [[Hal Willner]], [[Kip Hanrahan]], [[Leonard Bernstein]], [[Elli Medeiros]], [[Haydee Milanes]], Suylen Milanes, [[Los Van Van]], and [[Alabama Three]].\n\nSome of these collaborations appear on his retrospective album ''Improve the Shining Hour'', which also features his film and TV music for ''ABC News'', ''20/20'' and ''Turning Point''. He has produced albums for composer/saxophonists [[Tim Berne]] and Peter Gordon, and for the French avant-rock band Tanger. He co-wrote [[Joan Osborne]]'s Grammy-nominated song \"Spider Web\" from her triple platinum album ''[[Relish (album)|Relish]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nLucas was born in [[Syracuse, New York|Syracuse]], New York.<ref name=\"nndb\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nndb.com/people/183/000094898 |title=Gary Lucas |website=Nndb.com |date=1997-04-25 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> He obtained a degree in English from [[Yale University]] (1974),<ref name=\"nndb\"/> before establishing his career in music first as a college DJ and then as music director at the college radio station, WYBC FM.<ref name=\"garylucas.com\"/> Lucas is [[Jewish]].<ref>Jewish Themes - Gary Lucas - Official Website\ngarylucas.com/www/jthemes/Don Van Vliet with his \"Jewish guitar army\" (left Gary Lucas guitar, center ... Paul Wegener and Carl Boese), on a commission from BAM/New Music America.</ref>\n\nAccording to his website,<ref name=\"garylucas.com\"/> Lucas was encouraged by his father to try the guitar at the age of nine,<ref name=guitarhoo>{{cite web|title=Gary Lucas Interview|url=http://www.guitarhoo.com/interviews/gary-lucas-206!|website=Guitarhoo.com|accessdate=February 22, 2014|date=January 26, 2014}}</ref> briefly dabbled with other instruments at school, and played in groups during his teens in the 1960s.\n\n==Captain Beefheart==\nDuring his last year in high school he played for the documentary film unit of the Upstate Medical Center and wrote the musical score on his first film assignment. He travelled on what he calls a \"pilgrimage\"<ref name=\"garylucas.com\"/> to see childhood hero [[Captain Beefheart]], with whom he became close friends. From being a Beefheart fan, he eventually became his co-manager<ref name=\"beefheart\">[http://www.beefheart.com/datharp/albums/mbmembers/lucas.htm ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070202124508/http://www.beefheart.com/datharp/albums/mbmembers/lucas.htm |date=February 2, 2007 }}</ref> and occasionally performed on stage during the 1980\u201381 tours \u2013 reciting a poem (usually \"One Man Sentence\", sometimes \"Untitled\") or performing the solo guitar piece \"Flavor Bud Living\".<ref name=\"beefheart\" />\n\nAfter gaining his degree, Lucas played for a few years with the O-Bay-Gone Band<ref name=\"nndb\" /> before gaining a significant step in his career during 1980\u201382, when he was engaged to record on two Beefheart albums released by [[Virgin Records]],<ref name=\"nndb\" /><ref name=\"garylucas.com\"/> on one of which he was full-time lead alongside [[Moris Tepper]].<ref name=\"beefheart\" /> Lucas performed over a period of five years with the last incarnation of Beefheart's [[The Magic Band|Magic Band]]. His solo guitar pieces on ''[[Doc at the Radar Station]]'' (1980) and ''[[Ice Cream for Crow]]'' (1982) were his renditions of Beefheart's instrumental compositions, \"Flavor Bud Living\" and \"Evening Bell\".\n\nAfter Captain Beefheart retired in the 1980s, Lucas continued to be associated with the Magic Band's former members. Several of Beefheart's former band members reformed the group, touring as the Magic Band from 2003\u20132006. Their 2007 double album and DVD, ''21st Century Mirror Men'', followed up their debut album ''Back to the Front'', which was chosen as one of the best albums of 2004 by ''[[The Wire (magazine)|The Wire]]''. In 1988, Lucas performed at New York's ''[[Knitting Factory]]''. Shortly after, he was invited to appear at the 1988 [[JazzFest Berlin]].\n\nIn 2006 Lucas co-led a Beefheart tribute band, Fast 'n' Bulbous: the Captain Beefheart Project, which appeared at the Frankfurt Jazz Festival and the Jazz Em Agosto Festival in [[Lisbon]] during 2006. Their debut album ''Pork Chop Blue Around the Rind'' was profiled on NPR and charted on college radio in the United States. In Fall 2006, they toured Europe extensively, selling out shows at the London Jazz Festival, in Amsterdam's [[Bimhuis]], as well as playing in [[Bern]], Switzerland; [[Vienna]] and [[Schwaz]], Austria; and [[Ljubljana]], [[Slovenia]]. The group released its second album, ''Waxed Oop'', on [[Cuneiform Records]] in 2008.\n\nIn 2006, Lucas toured Europe with Phillip Johnston and five other jazz musicians as the Gary Lucas and Phillip Johnston Septet. The group performed jazz arrangements of Captain Beefheart's work in London, Amsterdam, Bern, Vienna, Schwaz (Austria) and Ljubljana.\n\n2017 marked the 50th anniversary of the release of Beefheart's album ''Safe as Milk,'' and saw Lucas engaged in numerous projects to mark the occasion. This included feature coverage in MOJO Magazine<ref>http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/mojo1711.jpg</ref> that coincided with the Captain Beefheart Weekend in Liverpool, England, where Lucas served on a panel at the participating Bluecoat Gallery. Lucas also collaborated with a group of Danish musicians for a Captain Beefheart tribute EP in 2017. In collaboration with Dutch DJ/producer Co de Cloet, the final interview given by Don Van Vliet was set to music composed by Lucas. Titled \"I Have a Cat,\" it was released on OkayMusic.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://soundcloud.com/garylucas/i-have-a-cat-excerpt-don-van-vliet-interview-w-co-de-kloet-music-by-gary-lucas | title=\"I Have a Cat\" excerpt--Don van Vliet interview w/ Co de Kloet set to music by Gary Lucas}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2017, the new Captain Beefheart tribute ensemble The World of Captain Beefheart, led by Lucas and Nona Hendryx, performed an album teaser performance at the Public Theater. The self-titled album was released in November 2017 on Knitting Factory Records.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/twocb/twocb.shtml | title=Gary Lucas - Official Website}}</ref> January 22, 2018 saw a special multimedia performance of The World of Captain Beefheart at City Winery NYC.\n\n==Collaborations==\nLucas first met Jeff Buckley in New York at the 1990 [[Tim Buckley]] tribute concert. Jeff Buckley stayed in New York and joined Lucas's band, Gods and Monsters. Lucas composed solo guitar instrumentals for \"Rise Up to Be\" and \"And You Will\", which later became the musical templates for \"Grace\" and \"Mojo Pin\",<ref name=\"garylucas.com\"/> which Lucas co-wrote with Buckley for his popular and critically acclaimed album ''[[Grace (Jeff Buckley album)|Grace]]''.<ref name=\"My Favourite Album\">{{cite web | url = http://www.abc.net.au/myfavouritealbum/top100.htm | title = My Favourite Album | accessdate = 2006-12-03 | date = 2006-12-03 | publisher = Australian Broadcasting Corporation}}</ref><ref>#1 Modern Rock Classic of all Time [[Mojo (magazine)]], 2006</ref> Early collaborations can also be heard on the Jeff Buckley and Gary Lucas album ''[[Songs to No One 1991\u20131992|Songs to No One]]'', which charted internationally with worldwide sales approaching 100,000. In the film ''Greetings from Tim Buckley''] (2013), [[Penn Badgely]] plays Buckley, and Tony Award winner Frank Wood plays Gary Lucas.  Emily Duff (her last name then was her maiden name) replaced Jeff Buckley as lead singer after he left to start his solo career.\n\nIn the mid-90s Lucas performed with [[Richard Barone]] in series of duo shows and live radio broadcasts in which Barone played [[Mellotron]]. Barone also guested on lead vocals with Lucas in his band [[Gods and Monsters (band)|Gods and Monsters]] and appears on subsequent albums.\n\nIn May 2011, Lucas released a new studio album with [[Gods and Monsters (band)|Gods and Monsters]], entitled ''The Ordeal of Civility''.<ref name=SDollar>{{cite news| url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052748703992704576305461484157844?mod=WSJ_LifeStyle_Lifestyle_5 | work=The Wall Street Journal | first=Steve | last=Dollar | title=Gods, Monsters and Guitars | date=May 5, 2011}}</ref> Gods and Monsters celebrated their 25th anniversary in June 2014 with a special performance at [[(Le) Poisson Rouge]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://the-guitar.com/gary-lucas-gods-and-monsters-25th-anniversary-concert/ |title=Gary Licas & Gods and Monsters 25th Anniversary Concert |date=June 28, 2014 |website=The-guitar.com |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref>\n\nIn 2003\u20132004 Lucas collaborated with Dutch lutist [[Jozef van Wissem]] on ''the Universe of Absence'' and ''Diplopia''. They have performed live on Dutch national TV together.\n\nIn 2007, Lucas collaborated on an album with underground electronic producer James R Hunter's project [[The Dark Poets]],  produced by British label manager [[Stevo Pearce]] of [[Some Bizzare Records]]. The album, ''Gary Lucas vs the Dark Poets \u2013 Beyond the Pale'', features an eclectic mixture of moody drum and bass, techno and rock tracks (notably \"Prime Time\", featuring vocals by Sarah Hilliard and James R. Hunter) as well as many early Lucas tracks and collaborations (including \"Procuress from Karmelitska Street\" featuring vocalist Pat Fulgoni of [[Kava Kava (band)|Kava Kava]] and original sketches of songs that went on to be used on Jeff Buckley's ''Grace'' album, including \"[[Grace (Jeff Buckley song)|Grace]]\" and \"[[Mojo Pin]]\").\n\nIn 2009, Lucas collaborated on a world music collaboration with Indian vocalist [[Najma Akhtar]]. Their album ''RISHTE'' combines rock, blues, folk, and [[raga]], on [[Harmonia Mundi]]/World Village. It was number 4 in the European World Music charts in 2009.<ref name=\"World Music Charts Europe\">{{cite web | url= http://www.wmce.de/?chartUrlMonth=9&chartUrlYear=2009 | title = World Music Charts Europe | accessdate = 2010-01-18 | publisher = [[European Broadcasting Union]]}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, he collaborated with Juan Galeano on his album ''El Peregrino'', which debuted April 2010.\n\nIn 2010, Lucas collaborated with vocalist Dean Bowman on their \"spiritual roots project\" and gospel album, \"CHASE THE DEVIL\". The duo performed an amalgam of Hebrew and African American blues live in the United States and Europe.\n\nIn 2013 Lucas performed in several special collaborations in late 2013, including with Mother Falcon and [[Amanda Palmer]], with Richard Mader and Pat Fulgoni as the Ghosts of Prague at Jazz Dock, and with Toni Deszo, deBORT's lead saxophonist, at the Budapest Jazz Club.<ref name=\"garylucas.com\"/>\n\nIn 2013, Lucas performed with his 1930s Chinese pop project, the Edge of Heaven, in a sold-out show at the Fishman Space at BAM with vocalists Sally Kwok and Mo Hai Jing and his group Gods and Monsters.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lucas|first=Gary|title=Gary Lucas: Tour|url=http://garylucas.com/www/dates/|website=Garylucas.com|accessdate=2012-05-12}}</ref> The project was also performed as a trio featuring Lucas, Sally Kwok, and Mo Hai Jing at the 1930 Club in Shanghai. October also say Lucas performing in [[Federico Garc\u00eda Lorca]]'s \"La Casa de Bernarda Alba\" at the Gaia Arts Center in Havana.\n\nIn 2014, Lucas released an album called ''Otherworld'' on Esoteric Antenna. ''Otherworld'' is a collaborative effort with [[Peter Hammill]] of [[Van der Graaf Generator]].<ref name=\"guitarhoo\"/>\n\nIn 2014 ''Fleischerei: Music From Max Fleischer Cartoons,'' a collaboration between Lucas, [[Tony Award]]-nominee [[Sarah Stiles]], and Joe Fiedler, is a musical tribute to [[Max Fleischer]] and the jazz and swing scores that accompanied his animated work. Their public debut came at the [[Brooklyn Academy of Music]] Cafe in November 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wPxWjcwzWzk |title=Gary Lucas' Fleischerei: Music from Betty Boop at BAM cafe NYC |publisher=[[YouTube ]]|date=2014-11-16 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> The project features Stiles as [[Betty Boop]]. An album of the songs was released on February 5, 2015 on Cuneiform Records.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/fleischerei/fleischerei.shtml | title=Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015 Lucas's psychedelic world music trio, Pearly Clouds, released their debut album on Discovery Records on March 15, 2015.<ref name=\"pearlyclouds.com\">{{Cite web|url=http://pearlyclouds.com/|title=\u52b9\u679c\u691c\u8a3c\uff01DUO\u30af\u30ec\u30f3\u30b8\u30f3\u30b0\u30d0\u30fc\u30e0\u30af\u30ea\u30a2\u3067\u6bdb\u7a74\u306f\u7121\u304f\u306a\u308b\uff1f26\u6b73\u306e\u9854\u51fa\u3057\u53e3\u30b3\u30df|website=Pearlyclouds.com}}</ref> The project features Hungarian traditional folk vocalist Enik\u0151 Szab\u00f3 and Serbian saxophonist Toni Dezso.\n\nLucas traveled to England in February 2017 to produce a new album from [[Ed Laurie]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.garylucas.com/photos.shtml |title = Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref> Lucas's celebrated album ''Rishte'' with Najma Akhtar was reissued on OkayMusic, rising to #4 on the World Music Charts Europe.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/ng/ |title = Gary Lucas :: Najma Akhtar and Gary Lucas|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref> Fall 2017 saw the release of the album \"Gary and Toni Go Nutz!\", a duo recording of songs and improvisation by Lucas and Toni Dezso of Pearly Clouds, on Rare Lumiere and Okay Records. Rokus Kalapis created an animated feature to accompany the album.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MI8WqmgvIP0|title=CYBERPUNK - music by Gary Lucas and T\u00f3ni Dezs\u0151, visuals by R\u00f3kus Kalapis|publisher=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n\nLucas began working on a follow-up to his celebrated album ''The Edge of Heaven'' with vocalist Feifei Yang and saxophonist Jason Candler<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://soundcloud.com/garylucas/a-tale-of-the-mah-jong-game-gary-lucas-w-feifei-yang-and-jason-candler |title = \"A Tale of the Mah-Jong Game\"-Gary Lucas, Feifei Yang & Jason Candler|website=Soundcloud.com}}</ref> in late 2017, including a version of Lucas and Buckley's \"Grace.\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://vimeo.com/243361252 | title=\"GRACE\" in MANDARIN--GARY LUCAS, FEIFEI YANG and JASON CANDLER @ 2017 NYC JEFF BUCKLEY TRIBUTE|website=Vimeo.com| date=2017-11-17}}</ref> At the annual Moon Festival, at Lincoln Center's Alice Tully Hall, Lucas and Yang performed with the 70-piece Asian Cultural Orchestra, including the debut of their duet of \"The Moon Represents My Heart.\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://vimeo.com/244536918 | title=Feifei Yang and Gary Lucas Live at the Moon Festival NYC 9/15/17--\"The Moon Represents My Heart\"| date=2017-11-26}}</ref> In celebration of the Chinese New Year in February 2018, the new Edge of Heaven trio performed at the Laurie Beechman Theatre.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/edgelive/edgelive.shtml | title=Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://vimeo.com/258619596 | title=\"GRACE\" --GARY LUCAS&#039; THE EDGE OF HEAVEN LIVE @ the Laurie Beechman Theatre NYC 2/16/18 Chinese New Year| date=2018-03-05}}</ref> Yang and Lucas also served as judges on CCTV's \"Super Baby\" talent competition and a documentary about their collaborations is forthcoming on SinoVision.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://vimeo.com/249453847 | title=Gary Lucas & Feifei Yang after judging CCTV&#039;s new talent show \"Super Baby\" 12/16/17| date=2018-01-02}}</ref>\n\nEarly in 2018, Lucas performed his Buckley tribute \"Touched by Grace\" with Jolene Grunberg in Amsterdam.\n\n==Solo projects==\n[[File:Gary Lucas at UN.jpeg|thumbnail|right|Gary Lucas performs before the General Assembly of the United Nations on International Holocaust Remembrance Day, January 27, 2017.Photo by Jason Candler]]\nDuring his fourth tour of Russia in 2005, Lucas performed his original solo guitar adaptation of the Lucas/Horn score accompanying the silent classic German horror film ''[[The Golem: How He Came into the World|The Golem]]'' (1920) in Moscow and Saint Petersburg and appeared on national TV before an estimated 50 million viewers, as well as being feted in the Russian edition of ''[[Rolling Stone]]''. He's played with ''The Golem'' solo globally since the live debut of the duet score he and keyboardist Walter Horn wrote for the movie in 1989 for the [[Brooklyn Academy of Music]] Next Wave Festival. He has performed it at the [[Venice Biennale]], London's [[Royal Festival Hall]], the New York Jewish Film Festival at [[Lincoln Center]], as part of a weeklong artist-in-residency at the [[Quebec City Summer Festival]], at the ''Alien'' artist [[H. R. Giger]]'s Retrospective in Prague (home of the Golem), at Atlanta's [[Dragon Con]] 2002, the largest science fiction festival in the world, and at the fifth annual [[Pop Montreal]] music and film festival.\n\nOther recent concert appearances include a concert at the Czech Embassy in Washington, D.C., by invitation of the Czech ambassador spotlighting Lucas's solo guitar arrangements of Czech classical music in honor of the 14th anniversary of the [[Velvet Revolution]].\n\nGary Lucas's January 2012 solo tour of Europe began in Spain with a program on National Basque Radio Euskadi, and a performance of the \"Spanish Dracula for Bilbao's Musiketan Festival\" in Sala BBK. In England, Lucas conducted his Captain Beefheart Symposium two nights in a row at Liverpool's Philharmonic and record 8 tracks in a collaboration with [[Bryan Ferry]] at Olympia Studios.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lucas|first=Gary|title=Captain Beefheart Symposium|url=http://garylucas.com/www/capt/|website=Garylucas.com|accessdate=2012-05-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Towie|first=Steve|title=Review: Captain Beefheart Symposium|url=http://www.sevenstreets.com/music-and-listening/review-captain-beefheart-symposium/|accessdate=2012-05-12|newspaper=Seven Streets|date=2012-01-21}}</ref> Two solo performances followed in [[Lisbon]] and [[Porto]], Portugal, with guest performer Diana Silviera.<ref>{{cite web|author=Alexandre Elias |url=https://www.dn.pt/inicio/artes/interior.aspx?content_id=2266284&seccao=M%FAsica |title=Concerto - Gary Lucas, um her\u00f3i da guitarra, ao vivo na ZDB - M\u00fasica - DN |website=Dn.pt |date=2012-01-27 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://issuu.com/metro_portugal/docs/20120127_pt_lisbon |title=20120127_pt_lisbon by metro portugal |website=Issuu.com |date= |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> The tour finished in Paris with a surprise performance at La Feline, and solo show at the New Morning with Cheyenne Schiavone, Beatrice Demi-Mondaine, Jean-Francis Pauvros, and Daniel Yvinec,<ref>{{cite web|last=Lucas|first=Gary|title=Solo and Acoustic Shows|url=http://www.garylucas.com/solo.shtml|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref> reviewed favorably by E. Corvee, 12 February 2012, in [[Politis (France)|''Politis'']]''.''<ref>{{cite news|last=Corvee|first=Elodie|title=je ne rentre dans aucune categorie|url=http://www.politis.fr/Gary-Lucas-Je-ne-rentre-dans,17002.html|accessdate=2012-05-12|newspaper=Politis|date=2012-02-01}}</ref>\n\nLucas returned to Europe for a debut solo in [[Sardinia]] at the Santa Arresi Jazz Festival, and a special concert at the [[Paradiso (Amsterdam)|Paradiso]] in Amsterdam on September 2, 2012, in a collaboration with the [[Metropole Orkest]] and Dutch singers entitled \"The music of Jeff Buckley and Gary Lucas\" and featuring Italian vocalist Alessio Franchini;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Wpxf3GhGXpg |title=Gary Lucas & Metropole Orchestra - Mojo Pin - Amsterdam 09-02 2012 |publisher=[[YouTube]] |date=2012-09-03 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> this coincided with publication of his first book, ''Touched by Grace\u2014La Mia Musica con Jeff Buckley''. He then performed a week of shows in the Czech Republic, headlining Prague's Alternativa Festival<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alternativa-festival.cz/detail-en/gary-lucas-j-h-michal-nejtek |title=Alternativa 2015: 23rd issue of music festival. 7\u201414/11 Prague |website=Alternativa-festival.cz |date= |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> solo, appearing live for three hours of interviews and performance on national Beat Radio, performing in [[Jablonec nad Nisou|Jablonec]], [[Bohemia]], with his \"Monsters from the Id\" music and film project.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/id/ |title=monsters from the id |website=Garylucas.com |date=2006-10-28 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> He also performed at [[Shakespeare and Company (bookstore)|Shakespeare and Company]], the legendary [[Paris]] bookstore.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://united-mutations.blogspot.com/2012/10/gary-lucas-at-durango-film-festival.html |title=United Mutations: GARY LUCAS AT THE DURANGO FILM FESTIVAL 2012 10 19 |website=United-mutations.blogspot.com |date=2012-10-14 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref>\n\n''Fleischerei'' was performed throughout 2016 at the Jewish Film Festival in Washington, D.C., the Porgy and Bess Jazz Club in Wien, the Boston Jewish Film Festival, the City Winery NYC and City Winery Chicago seders, as well as at the City Winery NYC klemzer brunch.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n\nLucas headlined the Pisa Internet Festival<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.internetfestival.it/en/ |title = Home - IF2019}}</ref> with a solo acoustic concert at Teatro Lumiere. He also performed with guest vocalist Danae Villanueva Blanco at the Gaia Arts Center Havana Cuba in May 2016.<ref>http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/granma5-13-16.jpg</ref> In December 2016, Lucas reunited with members of Plastic People of the Universe, DG 307, and Urfaust at the Blues Bahnof Prague.\n\nOn October 1, 2016, Lucas performed an acoustic solo concert to close the Jewish Museume of Vienna's exhibition \"Stars of David.\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://vimeo.com/188006251 | title=Gary Lucas Live at the Jewish Museum of Vienna 10/1/16 \"Stars of David\" Concert| date=2016-10-19}}</ref>\n\nFor Holocaust Remembrance Day 2017, Lucas performed solo before the General Assembly of the United Nations.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://vimeo.com/201390227 | title=Jan.27.17 Holocaust Memorial Ceremony GUITARIST GARY LUCAS (1)| date=2017-01-28}}</ref>\n\nA solo tour of Europe in 2017 also saw Lucas perform in Czech director Pavel Gobl's forthcoming ''The Supervision of the Interpretation of Dreams,'' as well as performances at the Varnsdorf State Theater and the Danish National Library. Lucas was honored to celebrate the 150th show at Pori, Finland's underground club Validi Karkia.<ref name=\"youtube1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aoeVyJZCSjo|title=Gary Lucas & Miryam LaTrece \"In The Cantina\" a Jeff Buckley Tribute -Recoletos Jazz-|publisher=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Lucas was featured in a two-part special on Co de Kloet's \"Co Live\" program on Dutch radio NPO, looking back over Gary's career.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://soundcloud.com/garylucas/colive-gary-lucas-special-on-npo-radio-2-part-one |title = CoLive! Gary Lucas Special on NPO Radio 2 part one|website=Soundcloud.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://soundcloud.com/garylucas/colive-gary-lucas-special-on-npo-radio-2-part-two |title = CoLive! Gary Lucas Special on NPO Radio 2 part two|website=Soundecloud.com}}</ref>\n\n2018 will see Lucas embark on a solo tour of multi-media performances titled \u201cAn Evening with Gary Lucas: From Beefheart to Buckley and Beyond,\u201d including 12 dates in [http://garylucas.com/www/dates/UK_Tour_2018.jpg May 2018 in the UK]<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/fbbb/fbbb.shtml |title = Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref><ref>http://garylucas.com/www/dates/UK_Tour_2018.jpg</ref>\n\n==Tribute performances==\n[[File:Gary Lucas performing.jpg|thumbnail|right|Gary Lucas performing \"The Music of Jeff Buckley and Gary Lucas\" with The Metropole Orchestra at Paradiso Amsterdam on September 2, 2012. Photo: Sjaniek Schaap]]\nLucas returned to New York City to play with the [[Les Paul Trio]] and singer [[Jann Klose]] in NYC's Iridium Jazz Club, with high-profile solo appearances at [[(Le) Poisson Rouge]] and [[Joe's Pub]] with [[M'Lumbo]] as well as on their new release ''Popular Science'', and headlining a tribute to avant-garde band [[The Shaggs]] at [[The Bellhouse]] in Brooklyn, where he performed with Gods and Monsters. The year wrapped with a trip to Havana\u2014Lucas' fifth appearance there\u2014where he performed three nights at the Gaia Arts Center in a tribute to [[Michelangelo Antonioni]] on the occasion of his 100th anniversary; performed live on national [[Radio Havana]] and [[Radio Ta\u00edno]]; and was interviewed and filmed performing live by national Austrian television ORF for a program which aired 2013.\n\nAdditional touring in 2013 included special performances focused on well-known collaborators [[Jeff Buckley]] and [[Captain Beefheart]]. Lucas performed a tribute concert to Buckley at the Barezzi Festival in [[Parma]], Italy, with Vinicio Caposella and Alessio Franchini, where he was also presented with a Lifetime Achievement Award. Lucas performed with the Metropole Orkest at the Paradiso in Amsterdam as part of \"The World of Captain Beefheart\", a tribute to Captain Beefheart (Don Van Vliet), that also featured [[Nona Hendryx]], Jolene Grunberg, and Tom Trapp.\n\nLucas returned to Italy in Summer 2015, performing across the country with Italian singer/songwriter Alessio Franchini, including as part of Franchini's ''Touch of Grace'' Tribute to Jeff Buckley at the Teatro della Luna in Milan, as well as an appearance at Italian singer-songwriter Vinicio Caposella's \"Moon in June Festival\" in Umbria.<ref>[http://www.lastampa.it/2015/03/19/multimedia/spettacoli/lucas-cos-ho-scritto-grace-con-jeff-buckley-8HmFj65dDfAmoM74hkD1VO/pagina.html] {{dead link|date=January 2020}}</ref><ref>http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/larepubjbt.jpg</ref>\n\nIn 2015 Lucas led Gods and Monsters as Music Director of ''A State of Grace'', a multi-artist tribute to both Tim and Jeff Buckley.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.stateofgracelive.com |title = Mystic Forest Shower Curtain Sets,Hand Knotted Area Rug,Cute White Food Pillow Perfect Cushion}}</ref> The tribute saw Gary perform with singer/songwriter [[Martha Wainwright]], [[Steve Kilbey]] (of [[The Church (band)]]), and other vocalists over 6 nights in Sydney, Melbourne, Canberra and at the Brisbane Festival.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://themusic.com.au/music/livereviews/2015/09/29/a-state-of-grace-enmore-theatre-luke-saunders/ |title = /}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2012, Lucas performed live before an estimated viewing audience of 70 million [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EzUDjINbgfs on CNBC] in a segment devoted to Gibson Guitars; later that summer the national French ARTE Channel interviewed him for the documentary [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m1-k-7v634I \"Rock Attitude\"]. He was also interviewed and filmed performing live by National Austrian Television ORF for a program which will air in 2013.\n\nAt the [[Peace Hotel]] in November 2016, Lucas and collaborator Sally Kwok performed a tribute Chinese pop of the 1930s. Later that month, Lucas performed as part of the \"Hendrix in Harlem\" Tribute at the Apollo Theater, alongside Fishbone, Nona Hendryx, and Ernie Isley.\n\n2017 saw Lucas pay tribute to Buckley over two nights at Recoletos Jazz Club in Madrid alongside Mercedes Ferrer and Miryam Latrece.<ref name=\"youtube1\"/> In September, Lucas performed a sold-out tribute to Buckley in London with special guest Mari Conti.<ref>[https://continuouscruiser.com/2017/11/23/when-gary-lucas-met-jeff-buckley/] {{dead link|date=January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Lectures, classes, symposia==\nLucas has spoken widely on his life and career. He also lectures widely on the mechanics of songwriting, extensive collaborations, composing for film, and the music business at the Amsterdam Music Conservatorum, [[Yale University]] (his alma mater), the [[University of Hawaii]], [[New York University]], and [[Columbia University]]. He has given guitar master classes since the late 1990s at such institutions as the Amsterdam Music Conservatory and in Honolulu at the [[University of Hawaii]]. He has also lectured at [[Rogers State University]] in Oklahoma, and [[McGill University]] in Montreal, Canada. In 2013, Lucas gave a [[TEDx]] talked titled \"Blues and the Tuning of the World.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TsfkHolImNE|title=Blues and the Tuning of the World: Gary Lucas at TEDxBergenCommunityCollege|publisher=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n\nIn Fall 2012, Lucas gave a masterclass and a concert in Paris with French guitarist David Konopnicki and his band at the Henri Dutilleux Music Conservatoire. In April 2014, Lucas gave a masterclass at Rutgers University Mason Gross School of the Arts, with students noting that \"his guitar playing and compositions were unlike anything else I have heard before\" and that \"he has some great ideas about life and music.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/mclass/ |title=masterclass |website=Garylucas.com|date=2013-01-03 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> December 2016 saw Lucas giving a Guitar Masterclass alongside a seminar on songwriting at [[Conservatorium van Amsterdam]]. Lucas has also given masterclasses at the [[School of Jazz at the New School]].\n\nWhile touring Mexico in 2014, Lucas was invited by the United States Ambassador to Mexico [[Earl Anthony Wayne]] to perform a concert at the Benjamin Franklin Library in [[Mexico City]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/bio/ |title=Official Website|website=Garylucas.com |date= |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> as part of the ambassador's outreach program for disadvantaged youth. Following the performance, Lucas received an official letter of endorsement and appreciation from Ambassador Wayne.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/mclass/mexico_letter1412.pdf |title=Letter from Embassy of the United States of America, Mexico |website=Garylucas.com |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> Lucas returned to perform again in December 2015 and November 2016, both at the invitation of the U.S. ambassador.\n\nLucas has continually conducted a popular symposium on his former mentor and collaborator, Captain Beefheart (Don Van Vliet), both in the U.S. and in Europe. The symposium focuses not only on Van Vliet's music, but also his work as a visual artist. Lucas discusses the history of Vliet's band, collaborations, personality, and techniques in addition to sharing archival footage and unreleased music.<ref name=\"http://garylucas.com/www/capt\">{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/capt/ |title=captain beefheart symposium |website=Garylucas.com |date=2010-12-19 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> His two symposia in Liverpool in January 2012 were sold out. He presented at the Zappanale in Bad Doberan, Germany in August 2012, followed by a reunion of jazz-rock Beefheart tribute ensemble Fast 'N' Bulbous co-led by Phillip Johnston.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lucas|first=Gary|title=Captain Beefheart Symposium Page|url=http://garylucas.com/www/capt/|website=Garylucas.com|accessdate=2012-05-05}}</ref>\n\nThe symposium has been given at numerous venues, including the [[Knitting Factory]] in Brooklyn, the Independent in San Francisco, [[Echoplex (venue)|Echoplex]] in Los Angeles, and Casa Del Lago in Mexico City, and often features notable guests, which have previously included Matt Groening, Robert Williams, Terry Van Vliet, Francis McCarthy, Gary Marker, Kristine McKenna, Bill Moseley, and many others.<ref name=\"http://garylucas.com/www/capt\"/>\n\nLucas was named Artist in Residence at Royal Liverpool Philharmonic Hall in Liverpool England in December, 2015.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://czb.ro/articol/10263/ |title = Articol: Gary Lucas is Artist in Residence at Royal Liverpool Philharmonic Hall - Revista de Muzica Online: ClickZoomBytes - CZB.ro}}</ref> During this residency, Lucas performed numerous solo works and presented his new Jeff Buckley Symposium.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/jbs/jbs.shtml |title = Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref>\n\n==Film and television scores==\nLucas has composed and performed live accompaniment for several films throughout his career,<ref name=\"garylucas1\">{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/film/ |title=live music and film projects |website=Garylucas.com |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> the first having been a score to the 1920 silent film ''[[The Golem: How He Came into the World]]'', composed with Walter Horn and debuted in 1989 at the [[Brooklyn Academy of Music]] Next Wave Festival. Since that premiere, a solo, guitar version of the accompaniment to ''The Golem'' has been performed at numerous venues and festivals around the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/golem/ |title=the golem |website=Garylucas.com |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> He has gone on to compose live guitar accompaniments for several films, sometimes in collaboration with other artists.<ref name=\"garylucas1\"/>\n\nThroughout 2013, Lucas extensively toured his live film accompaniments. His long-running live score to George Melford's ''[[Dr\u00e1cula (1931 Spanish-language film)|Dr\u00e1cula]]'' was performed at the [[Jerusalem Film Festival]], the Silent Movie Theatre in Hollywood, the Cineteca Nacional in Mexico City, the [[United Palace]] Theatre in Harlem, Kino Aero in [[Prague]], and Kino Siska in [[Slovenia]].<ref name=\"garylucas.com\">{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/bio/ |title=biography |website=Garylucas.com |date=2013-10-05 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> Lucas's live score to [[Jos\u00e9 Mojica Marins]]' \"Esta Noite Encarnerei no teu Cadaver\" saw its European debut at the [[Melkweg]] in Amsterdam in May 2013.<ref name=\"garylucas.com\"/>\n\nLucas has continued to perform his live film accompaniments, including ''Monsters of the Id'' at [[Monsterpalooza]] in Burbank, and ''This Night I will Possess Your Corpse'' at the [[Wexner Center for the Arts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wexarts.org/performing-arts/esta-noite-encarnarei-no-teu-cadaver-night-i-will-possess-your-corpse |title=Esta Noite Encarnarei no Teu Cadaver (This Night I Will Possess your Corpse) &#124; Wexner Center for the Arts |website=Wexarts.org |date=2014-03-01 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> He also premiered live accompaniment to the 1934 silent, Chinese film ''[[The Goddess (1934 film)|The Goddess]]'' in early 2014. Fall of 2014 saw the premiere of new live scores to ''[[Frankenstein (1931 film)|Frankenstein]]'' and ''[[Vampyr]]''.\n\nIn Fall 2009, Gary Lucas debuted his new live program of solo guitar arrangements of famous film music at the 5th [[Jecheon International Music & Film Festival]] in [[South Korea]]. He was also invited by the Festival Internacional del Nuevo Cine Latinoamerica to preview his score for the Spanish version of ''Dracula'' (1931) at the 31st [[Havana Film Festival]] in Havana, Cuba.<ref name=\"Gary Lucas Under the Skin of Dracula\">{{cite web | url= http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/Granma_Dec09.pdf | title = Gary Lucas Under the Skin of Dracula\" (English trans. of article in Spanish, \"Lucas bajo la piel de Dracula\" in the Havana newspaper ''Granma Culturales'', 12/14/09.)| accessdate = 2010-01-18|publisher=[[Granma (newspaper)|Granma]]}}</ref> Lucas performs the European premiere of his Spanish \"Dracula\" project at the 9th [[Transylvania International Film Festival]] in [[Cluj-Napoca]], Romania, on May 30, 2010, in the open-air outside the Banfi Botzida Castle.\n\nLucas returned to Cuba in December 2010 for the 32nd [[Havana Film Festival]], and debuted a new live score accompanying a Brazilian horror classic, ''Esta Noite Encarnerei no teu Cadaver'' (\"Tonight I will Possess Your Corpse\").<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.habanafilmfestival.com/noticias/index.php?newsid=469 |title=Festival Internacional del Nuevo Cine Latinoamericano |language=es |website=Habanafilmfestival.com |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Gary performed his live solo score to [[The Goddess (1934 film)]], originally premiered at Foundation Botin in Santander, Spain, at [[Pioneer Works]] in Red Hook Brooklyn.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/goddess/goddess.shtml |title = Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref> His live accompaniment to ''[[The Exterminating Angel]]'', which premiered at the Havana Film Festival in 2011, was also debuted in the United States at Pioneer Works.\n\n2017 saw the premiere at Roulette in Brooklyn of Gary's new live score for [[Orson Welles]]' 1938 silent classic ''Too Much Johnson.''<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/tmj/tmj.shtml |title = Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref> A new film score set to a fragment of the Russian futurist avant-garde short ''Shackled By Film'' (starring [[Vladimir Mayakovsky]] and [[Lilya Brik]] was premiered at [[Emir Kusturica]]'s [[Kustendorf International Film Festival]] in January 2018. In February 2018, Lucas returned to Roulette to premiere a new live film score to a collection of short films by visionary film director [[Curtis Harrington]]<ref name=\"ReferenceB\">{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/harrington/harrington.shtml |title = Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref>\n* ''[[The Golem: How He Came into the World]]'' with Walter Horn.\n* ''[[The Unholy Three (1925 film)|The Unholy Three]]'', commissioned by [[Film Society of Lincoln Center]]).\n* ''[[J'accuse! (1938 film)|J'accuse]]'' with Dutch-Iranian composer Reza Namavar, commissioned by the Netherlands Holland Festival.\n* ''[[The Exterminating Angel]]''\n* ''[[Dracula (1931 Spanish-language film)|Dracula]]'', the score Lucas has toured most frequently, having been performed at several film and music festivals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/dracula/ |title=spanish-language \"dracula\" |website=Garylucas.com |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref>\n* ''[[This Night I'll Possess Your Corpse]]''\n* ''[[The Goddess (1934 film)|The Goddess]]'' debuted at Fundaci\u00f3n Bot\u00edn in January 2014 as part of the \"Golden Age of Chinese Cinema\" series curated by [[Film Society of Lincoln Center]] Director Emeritus Richard Pena.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/goddess/ |title=The Goddess |website=Garylucas.com|date=2014-01-08 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref>\n* ''[[Vampyr]]'' was premiered at [[AFI Silver]] in fall of 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/vampyr/ |title=Vampyr |website=Garylucas.com |date=2014-11-01 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref>\n* ''[[Frankenstein (1931 film)|Frankenstein]]'' premiered at [[United Palace]] on Halloween 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/fstein/ |title=Frankenstein |website=Garylucas.com |date=2014-10-31 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref>\n* ''Cinefantastique'' (solo guitar arrangements of famous film music), named one of the Top 10 Roots Albums of 2013 by the Philadelphia City Paper<ref name=\"citypaper.net\">{{cite web|author= |url=http://citypaper.net/article.php?Top-10-roots-albums-of-2013-18224 |title=Top 10 roots albums of 2013 :: Cover :: Philadelphia City Paper |website=Citypaper.net |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> and Best Guitar Album of the year by Gapplegate Guitar and Bass Blog.<ref name=\"citypaper.net\"/>\n* ''[[Too Much Johnson]] premiered at Roulette Intermedium Brooklin in January 2017\n* ''The Short Films of Curtis Harrington'', a collection of short films accompanied by a live score by Lucas, premiered in February 2017 at Roulette Intermedium Brooklyn.<ref name=\"ReferenceB\"/>\n* ''American Faust: From Condi to Neo-Condi'' an award-winning documentary on [[Condoleezza Rice]], directed by [[Sebastian Doggart]], additional scoring\n* ''Trust Me'' (a [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]] documentary, original score)\n* ''Bed and Breakfast 9/11'' (an award-winning documentary shown on [[PBS]])\n* ''The Legacy of [[Jedwabne]]'' (documentary by [[S\u0142awomir Gr\u00fcnberg]])\n* ''[[LaLee's Kin: The Legacy of Cotton]]'' (an [[oscar nomination|Oscar-nominated]] [[Maysles Films]] documentary for [[HBO]], screened at the [[Museum of Modern Art]] in New York as part of their Maysles Films 50 Year Retrospective; [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] wrote: \"Gary Lucas' [[Delta blues]] guitar music adds vivid color to this report from America's forgotten underbelly\")\n* ''Dragon Boys'' (Canadian \"movie of the week\") 2007.\n* ''For Love and Honor'' (Erik Greenberg Anjou's documentary about American Ivy League collegiate football).\n* ''American Faust: From Condi to Neo-Condi'' (score, 2010)\n* In the early 2000s, Lucas performed a guitar rendition of the theme music to [[BBC1]] soap opera ''[[EastEnders]]''.\n* \"Farewell Angelina\" as performed by Lucas and [[Jeff Buckley]] was featured on [[Roadies (TV series)]].\n\n==Awards and honors==\n\nLucas was the subject of Klaus Totzler's [[documentary]] ''Gary Lucas in Havana'', which aired on Austrian national television ORF and on 3SAT TV in May 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NcwX-lKII6g |title=Gary Lucas on 3sat mediathek Austrian TV |publisher=[[YouTube]] |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref>\n\nIn the last few years Lucas has been profiled in the ''[[International Herald Tribune]]'', ''Lib\u00e9ration'', and featured on the cover of ''[[The Forward]]'' as well as the national Dutch newspaper ''[[Het Parool]]''. According to the Beefheart website: \"Since the end of the Magic Band, he has been very prolific in his own right, solo and within a band, releasing almost an album a year since 1991. His virtuoso solo live shows are awesome in the sounds he extracts from his guitar.\"<ref name=\"beefheart\" />\n\nIn 2009, [[Classic Rock (magazine)|''Classic Rock'']] named Lucas one of the \"100 Greatest Living Guitarists\".<ref>Classic Rock magazine, August 2009.</ref> In October 2013, Lucas received a Lifetime Achievement Award at the Barezzi Festival in Parma, Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://czb.ro/articol/6004/ |title=Articol: Gary Lucas in Paris, Bristol, London, Aberdeen, Edinburgh, Cork, Dublin, Mexico City, Prague, Budapest and Beyond - Revista De Muzica Online: ClickZoomBytes |website=Czb.ro |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> Lucas was given an Acker Award for Achievement in Avant Garde Music in June 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ackerawards.com/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140603192737/http://www.ackerawards.com/#!nyc-awards/canh|url-status=dead|title=\u30d5\u30ec\u30a4\u30a2\u30af\u30ea\u30cb\u30c3\u30af\u6a2a\u6d5c\u9662\u306e\u8a55\u5224\u3068\u53e3\u30b3\u30df\u304c\u30a2\u30a6\u30c8\u3002\u6599\u91d1\u3068\u4e88\u7d04|archivedate=June 3, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe U.S. Consul General of [[Milan]], [[Philip T. Reeker]], presented Lucas with the Consul General's Award for [[Cultural Diplomacy]] on March 21, 2015, following a special performance and reception at U.S. Consulate in Milan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/pr/pr_latest.html |title=Official Website |website=Garylucas.com |date=2015-10-25 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/grfx/consulate1503.jpg |format=JPG |title=Letter from Consulate General of the United States of America |website=Garylucas.com |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref>\n\nLucas received the Lifetime Achievement Award at the Premio Ciampi Festival in Tuscany, named for legendary Italian songwriter [[Piero Ciampi]], in December 2015.\n\nConsultant for ''[[Greetings from Tim Buckley]]'' about Jeff Buckley's early days working in NYC, directed by Dan Algrant and starring Penn Badgley (\"Gossip Girl\") as Jeff. Character of Gary Lucas played by Tony Award-winning actor Frank Wood. Lucas plays his own guitar parts for the film. The film was released worldwide in cinemas in 2013.<ref>{{cite news|last=Dickey|first=Josh L.|title=Frank Wood Aboard 'Buckley' |url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1118041626|publisher=Variety|accessdate=2012-05-01|date=2011-08-22}}</ref>\n\n==Writing==\n2013 saw the publishing of Lucas's book ''Touched by Grace: My Time with Jeff Buckley'' published in English by Jawbone Press.<ref name=\"jawbonepress.com\">{{cite web|url=http://jawbonepress.com/touched-by-grace/ |title=JAWBONE &#124; smart books for musical minds |website=Jawbonepress.com |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> In support of this, Lucas performed a string of shows in the United Kingdom, as well as two performances and signings at [[Shakespeare and Company (bookstore)|Shakespeare and Company]] in Paris.\n\nArcana Books (Italy) published Gary Lucas' book, ''Touched by Grace\u2014La Mia Musica con Jeff Buckley'', in September 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/tbg/ |title=touched by grace |website=Garylucas.com |date= |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> [http://www.elisarusso.com/gary-lucas-touched-by-grace-la-mia-musica-con-jeff-buckley-arcana/ The book received excellent reviews in the Italian press]. Publication was supported with several Italian in store appearances and concerts by Lucas, including Feltrinelli in [[Trieste]], the [[Fnac]] Megastore in Milan, and the Madame Guitar Festival in [[Tricesimo]] (Lucas' third appearance there). ''Touched by Grace'' was published in English by Jawbone Press in October 2013.<ref name=\"jawbonepress.com\"/> [[Mojo (magazine)|''Mojo'']] gave the book four stars.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/mojo1311.jpg |title=Touched By Grace : My Time With Jeff Buckley |author=Gary Lucas |website=Garylucas.com |accessdate=2014-07-12}}</ref> Roy Trakin of [[Hits (magazine)|''Hits'' (magazine)]] named the book among his top 10 of 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://addictedtonoise.com.au/roy-trakins-best-2014/ |title=Roy Trakin's Best of 2014 - Exiled Off Main Street - International Roots Music - Exiled Off Main Street \u2013 International Roots Music |website=Addictedtonoise.com.au |date=2014-12-17 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref>\n\nLucas has written extensively, working in poetry and fiction, as well as reflections on music and his own experiences.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/writings.shtml |title = Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nLucas draws from the [[blues]] tradition and includes styles such as [[psychedelic rock]], [[world music]], and [[jazz]], as well as [[classical music|classical]] works. ''[[The New York Times]]'' described his guitar playing: \"Gary Lucas plays guitar the way [[Salvador Dal\u00ed]] painted, with dazzling displays of technique, wicked humor, and a thirst to completely refashion his art from its basic elements\".<ref>New York Times, November 2000.</ref>\n\nLucas has been described as a \"guitarist with a global guitar\" (Larry Rohter, 9 May 2011, ''New York Times'') \"one of the best and most original guitarists in America\" (David Fricke, 16 November 2006, ''[[Rolling Stone]]''); a \"legendary leftfield guitarist\" (''[[The Guardian]]'', 24 December 2005); \"the thinking man's guitar hero\" (''[[The New Yorker]]'', 8 January 2007), \"perhaps the greatest living electric guitar player\" ([[Daniel Levitin]]) and one of \"the most innovative and challenging guitarists playing today\" (''[[fRoots]]'', March 2002). Lucas' style melds easily into rock and blues, has \"avant-garde affinities\", but is \"not easily typecast\" according to the [[The Wall Street Journal|''Wall Street Journal'']].<ref name=\"SDollar\" />\n\nLucas has collaborated intermittently with DJ Cosmo (Colleen Murphy) as Wild Rumpus. Having worked together in the Manhattan [[rave]] scene, their work focuses on incorporating Lucas's [[electric guitar]] work and various other genre influences into [[electronic dance music]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/wildr/ |title=Wild Rumpus |website=Garylucas.com |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> In 2014 the duo released the double-vinyl album ''Musical Blaze-up'' on Bitches Brew. Curious Animal gave the LP a seven out of ten, saying \"the international sound is the album's&nbsp;... big defining feature\".<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.curiousanimal.com/album-review-musical-blaze-up-by-wild-rumpus/ |title=Album Review: Musical Blaze-Up by Wild Rumpus - Curious Animal Magazine |website=Curiousanimal.com |date=2014-06-02 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> I House U called ''Musical Blaze-Up'' a \"rawkus musical [[mashup (music)|mash-up]]\" and the video for lead single \"Rock the Joint\" was named BBC 6 Music Video of the Week.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://acloserlisten.com/2014/04/02/spring-music-preview-part-ii/ |title=Spring Music Preview Part II |website=Acloserlisten.com |date=2014-04-02 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref>\n\nFebruary 2014 saw the release of ''Otherworld'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/oworld/ |title=Otherworld: Peter Hammill and |website=Garylucas.com |date=2014-04-13 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> an experimental collaboration between Lucas and [[Peter Hammill]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Thom Jurek |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/other-world-mw0002604043 |title=Other World - Peter Hammill,Gary Lucas &#124; Songs, Reviews, Credits, Awards |website=[[AllMusic]] |date=2014-02-03 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> The album was well received by critics, with ''MAX Magazine Italy'' writing, \"Guitars, abstract landscapes, breathtaking texts (as always when a true poet as Hammill gathers in the field), spectral songs, layers, all conspire to create something unexpectedly powerful and disarming\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/rvw_14.html#MAX1401 |title=reviews |website=Garylucas.com |date=2014-04-25 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> Lucas and Hammill were featured on the covers of ''Guitar Player'' magazine<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/gp1405.pdf |title=Guitar Player magazine article |website=Garylucas.com |accessdate=2014-07-12}}</ref> and ''Rock Society'' magazine<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/rs-cover1403.jpg |title=Rock Society magazine article |website=Garylucas.com |accessdate=2014-07-12}}</ref> for the project, in addition to featured coverage in ''Prog'' magazine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/prog1402.pdf |quote=He was the best live artist I saw when I first came to London in '73. He really made an impression on me |title=Lucas on Hammill : The Odd Couple |website=Garylucas.com |accessdate=2014-07-12}}</ref> ''[[Record Collector]]'' gave the album four stars (out of four),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://recordcollectormag.com/reviews/other-world |title=Other World - Record Collector Magazine |website=Recordcollectormag.com |date=2011-05-26 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> and [[Uncut (magazine)|''Uncut'']] marked it seven out of ten.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/uncut1404.jpg |title=Peter Hammill / Gary Lucas : Other World : Esoteric Antenna |website=Garylucas.com |accessdate=2014-07-12}}</ref> In support of the collaboration, Lucas and Hammill performed together at the Gouveia Art Rock Festival in Portugal and at the [[Teatro de la Ciudad]] in Mexico City.\n\n''The Edge of Heaven'', is an album of Lucas's lush arrangements of classic Chinese pop tunes from the 1930s, with a distinctly bluesy feel. It received positive international reviews from ''Rolling Stone'' to ''The Wall Street Journal'' to the ''Hong Kong Music Weekly''. It was #1 on the World Music Charts in Canada and garnered international attention, England's ''[[Q magazine|Q]]'' magazine awarding it 4 stars, and ''Mojo'' writing: \"It is simply gorgeous\". The album was chosen as one of the best discs of the year in France's ''[[Lib\u00e9ration]]'' newspaper. There was a lengthy profile for the album in ''The Wall Street Journal'', as well as an NPR interview. Lucas recently released an expanded concert version of ''The Edge of Heaven'' with his band, Gods and Monsters, and vocalists Sally Kwok and Mo Hai Jin, both from Shanghai.<ref name=\"garylucas.com\"/> The group received standing ovations at the [[Holland Festival]] in [[Amsterdam]] in June 2011.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lucas|first=Gary|title=Edge of Heaven Webpage|url=http://garylucas.com/epk/|website=Garylucas.com|accessdate=2012-05-06}}</ref>\n\n2016 saw the release of 3 new releases to positive critical response. ''Fleischerei: Music from Max Fleischer Cartoons'', featuring Joe Fiedler, Jeff Lederer, Michael Bates, Rob Garcia, and Sarah Stiles, was named \"One of the Best Albums of 2016\" by [[Down Beat]]<ref>http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/downbeat1612.jpg</ref> and \"One of the Best Indie Albums of 2016\" by [[Goldmine (magazine)]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.goldminemag.com/blogs/spin-cycle-blogs/spin-cycles-twelve-days-christmas-2016 |title = Spin Cycle's Twelve Days of Christmas, 2016|date = 2016-12-07}}</ref> ''Pearly Clouds'',<ref name=\"pearlyclouds.com\"/> an exploration of traditional Hungarian folk music, featuring saxophonist Toni Dezso and vocalist Eniko Szabo, was called \"a record of spiritual longing and timeless musical transcendence\" by [[FRoots]] and described as \"unusual and compelling listening\" by [[BBC Three]]. The acoustic folk pop collaboration with [[Jann Klose]], ''Stereopticon'' was given four stars by [[Mojo (magazine)]]. [[No Depression (magazine)]] wrote of the record, saying \"the harmonies, vocal interactions, and clear precise acoustic guitar provide the listener with enchanting listening.\u201d<ref>[http://www.lucasklose.com] {{dead link|date=January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Selected discography==\n* ''[[Skeleton at the Feast]]'' (1991)\n* ''[[Gods and Monsters (Gary Lucas album)|Gods and Monsters]]'' (1992)\n* ''[[Bad Boys of the Arctic]]'' (1994)\n* ''[[Pra\u017esk\u00e1 Stra\u0161idla (The Ghosts of Prague)]]'' with [[Urfaust]] (1996)\n* ''[[Evangeline (Gary Lucas album)|Evangeline]]'' (1997)\n* ''[[Busy Being Born]]'' (1998)\n* ''[[@ Paradiso]]'' (1999)\n* ''The Du-Tels \u2013 No Knowledge of Music Required'' with [[Peter Stampfel]] (2000)\n* ''[[Street of Lost Brothers]]'' (2000)\n* '' Level the Playing Field: Early HurlyBurly 1988\u20131994 '' (2000)\n* '' The Edge of Heaven (album)|The Edge of Heaven ''(2001)\n* ''[[Songs to No One 1991\u20131992]]'' with [[Jeff Buckley]] (2002)\n* '' Operators Are Standing By: The Essential Gary Lucas 1989-1996 '' (2003)\n* '' Diplopia '' (2003), with [[Jozef van Wissem]]\n* ''The Universe of Absence'' (2004) with Jozef van Wissem\n* ''Fast 'N' Bulbous \u2013 Pork Chop Blue Around the Rind'' (2005)\n* ''Coming Clean'' (2006)\n* ''Musical Blazeup'' (2007) with DJ Cosmo\n* ''Beyond the Pale'' (2008) with [[The Dark Poets]]\n* ''Chase the Devil'' (2008) with [[Dean Bowman]]\n* ''Rock the Joint'' (2008)  with [[Beardyman]]\n* ''Down the Rabbit Hole'' with [[Gerald Zbindin]] (2008)\n* ''Purple Somersault'' (2008) with DJ Cosmo\n* ''Fast 'n' Bulbous \u2013 Waxed Oop'' (2009)\n* ''Rishte'' [[Najma Akhtar]] & Gary Lucas (2009)\n* ''Music for the Eden Project''l single (2010)\n* '' The Ordeal of Civility '' (2011), released UK and Europe (2012)<ref name=\"Songwriter With Global Guitar\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/05/10/arts/music/gary-lucas-has-a-new-cd-the-ordeal-of-civility.html?_r=1&adxnnl=1&pagewanted=all&adxnnlx=1336812034-NRSQoxcvBMQwElVihb9i1g |author=Larry Richter |title=Songwriter With a Global Guitar |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref>\n* ''Gary Lucas Plays Bohemian Classics,'' Czech Republic, (2012)\n* ''Popular Science'' with [[M'Lumbo]],  (Pursuance, 2013)\n* ''Cinefantastique'',  (Northern Spy, 2013)\n* ''[[Other World (album)|Other World]]'' with [[Peter Hammill]] (Esoteric Antenna, 2014)\n* ''Fleischerei'' (Cuneiform, 2016)<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n* ''Pearly Clouds'' (Trapeze, 2016)\n* ''Stereopticon'' with Jann Klose (Cosmic Trigger, 2016)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/disc/ |title=Official Website |website=Garylucas.com |date= |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref>\n* ''The World of Captain Beefheart'' (Knitting Factory Records, 2017)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.garylucas.com/ Official website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070202124508/http://www.beefheart.com/datharp/albums/mbmembers/lucas.htm Lucas' biography and discography, on Captain Beefheart's \"band members\" section]\n* [https://www.nytimes.com/2011/05/10/arts/music/gary-lucas-has-a-new-cd-the-ordeal-of-civility.html?_r=1&pagewanted=all \"Songwriter with a Global Guitar\"] ''NY Times'' Review\n* {{YouTube|T-KS8p1vL_s|Edge of Heaven clip}}\n{{Gary Lucas|state=autocollapse}}\n{{Captain Beefheart}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lucas, Gary}}\n[[Category:Northern Spy Records artists]]\n[[Category:American blues guitarists]]\n[[Category:American male guitarists]]\n[[Category:American rock guitarists]]\n[[Category:Songwriters from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Syracuse, New York]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:Tzadik Records artists]]\n[[Category:The Magic Band members]]\n[[Category:Enemy Records artists]]\n[[Category:Guitarists from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:20th-century American guitarists]]\n[[Category:Knitting Factory Records artists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American musician}}\n{{about|the musician|the baseball player|Gary Lucas (baseball)|the rapper|Joyner Lucas}}\n{{Primary sources|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name             = Gary Lucas\n| image            =\n| caption          = Gary Lucas at the London Tribute to Jeff Buckley on September 9, 2017<br />Photo by Michael Ark\n| background    = solo_singer\n| birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|1952|6|20}}\n| birth_place     = [[Syracuse, New York|Syracuse]], New York, United States\n| genre             = [[Rock music|Rock]], [[experimental rock]], pop, blues\n| occupation     = Musician, singer-songwriter, producer\n| instrument     = Guitar\n| years_active  = 1970s\u2013present\n| label              = [[Knitting Factory Records|Knitting Factory]], [[Tzadik Records|Tzadik]], [[Enemy Records|Enemy]], [[Northern Spy Records|Northern Spy]]\n| associated_acts = [[Captain Beefheart]], [[Gods and Monsters (band)|Gods and Monsters]], the Du-Tels, Chase the Devil\n| website           = {{URL|www.garylucas.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Gary Lucas''' (born June 20, 1952) is an American guitarist who was a member of [[Captain Beefheart]]'s band. He formed the band [[Gods and Monsters (band)|Gods and Monsters]] in 1989.\n\nLucas has collaborated with [[Leonard Bernstein]], [[Jeff Buckley]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jeffbuckley.com/jbin/13-08.html |title=The Jeff Buckley International Newsletter |website=Jeffbuckley.com |accessdate=2014-07-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130929130026/http://www.jeffbuckley.com/jbin/13-08.html |archivedate=2013-09-29 }}</ref> [[John Cale]], [[Nick Cave]], [[David Johansen]], and [[Lou Reed]].\n\nHe has also worked with [[Chris Cornell]], [[The Dark Poets]], [[DJ Spooky]], [[Dr. John]], [[Amanda Palmer]], [[Bryan Ferry]], [[The Future Sound of London]], [[Allen Ginsberg]], [[Peter Hammill]], [[Warren Haynes]], [[Jann Klose]], [[Dave Liebman]], [[Joe Lovano]], [[Melissa Mars]], [[Kate & Anna McGarrigle]], [[Geoff Muldaur]], [[Bob Neuwirth]], [[Mary Margaret O'Hara]], [[Onetwo (band)|Onetwo]], [[Graham Parker]], [[Van Dyke Parks]], [[Iggy Pop]], [[Roswell Rudd]], [[Fred Schneider]], [[Richard Barone]], [[John Sebastian]], [[Adrian Sherwood]], [[Patti Smith]], [[Peter Stampfel]], [[Damo Suzuki]], [[Steve Swallow]], [[Matthew Sweet]], [[Bob Weir]], [[John Zorn]], [[Nona Hendryx]], [[Emir Kusturica]] and the [[No Smoking Orchestra]], [[Hal Willner]], [[Kip Hanrahan]], [[Leonard Bernstein]], [[Elli Medeiros]], [[Haydee Milanes]], Suylen Milanes, [[Los Van Van]], and [[Alabama Three]].\n\nSome of these collaborations appear on his retrospective album ''Improve the Shining Hour'', which also features his film and TV music for ''ABC News'', ''20/20'' and ''Turning Point''. He has produced albums for composer/saxophonists [[Tim Berne]] and Peter Gordon, and for the French avant-rock band Tanger. He co-wrote [[Joan Osborne]]'s Grammy-nominated song \"Spider Web\" from her triple platinum album ''[[Relish (album)|Relish]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nLucas was born in [[Syracuse, New York|Syracuse]], New York.<ref name=\"nndb\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nndb.com/people/183/000094898 |title=Gary Lucas |website=Nndb.com |date=1997-04-25 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> He obtained a degree in English from [[Yale University]] (1974),<ref name=\"nndb\"/> before establishing his career in music first as a college DJ and then as music director at the college radio station, WYBC FM.<ref name=\"garylucas.com\"/> Lucas is [[Jewish]].<ref>Jewish Themes - Gary Lucas - Official Website\ngarylucas.com/www/jthemes/Don Van Vliet with his \"Jewish guitar army\" (left Gary Lucas guitar, center ... Paul Wegener and Carl Boese), on a commission from BAM/New Music America.</ref>\n\nAccording to his website,<ref name=\"garylucas.com\"/> Lucas was encouraged by his father to try the guitar at the age of nine,<ref name=guitarhoo>{{cite web|title=Gary Lucas Interview|url=http://www.guitarhoo.com/interviews/gary-lucas-206!|website=Guitarhoo.com|accessdate=February 22, 2014|date=January 26, 2014}}</ref> briefly dabbled with other instruments at school, and played in groups during his teens in the 1960s.\n\n==Captain Beefheart==\nDuring his last year in high school he played for the documentary film unit of the Upstate Medical Center and wrote the musical score on his first film assignment. He travelled on what he calls a \"pilgrimage\"<ref name=\"garylucas.com\"/> to see childhood hero [[Captain Beefheart]], with whom he became close friends. From being a Beefheart fan, he eventually became his co-manager<ref name=\"beefheart\">[http://www.beefheart.com/datharp/albums/mbmembers/lucas.htm ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070202124508/http://www.beefheart.com/datharp/albums/mbmembers/lucas.htm |date=February 2, 2007 }}</ref> and occasionally performed on stage during the 1980\u201381 tours \u2013 reciting a poem (usually \"One Man Sentence\", sometimes \"Untitled\") or performing the solo guitar piece \"Flavor Bud Living\".<ref name=\"beefheart\" />\n\nAfter gaining his degree, Lucas played for a few years with the O-Bay-Gone Band<ref name=\"nndb\" /> before gaining a significant step in his career during 1980\u201382, when he was engaged to record on two Beefheart albums released by [[Virgin Records]],<ref name=\"nndb\" /><ref name=\"garylucas.com\"/> on one of which he was full-time lead alongside [[Moris Tepper]].<ref name=\"beefheart\" /> Lucas performed over a period of five years with the last incarnation of Beefheart's [[The Magic Band|Magic Band]]. His solo guitar pieces on ''[[Doc at the Radar Station]]'' (1980) and ''[[Ice Cream for Crow]]'' (1982) were his renditions of Beefheart's instrumental compositions, \"Flavor Bud Living\" and \"Evening Bell\".\n\nAfter Captain Beefheart retired in the 1980s, Lucas continued to be associated with the Magic Band's former members. Several of Beefheart's former band members reformed the group, touring as the Magic Band from 2003\u20132006. Their 2007 double album and DVD, ''21st Century Mirror Men'', followed up their debut album ''Back to the Front'', which was chosen as one of the best albums of 2004 by ''[[The Wire (magazine)|The Wire]]''. In 1988, Lucas performed at New York's ''[[Knitting Factory]]''. Shortly after, he was invited to appear at the 1988 [[JazzFest Berlin]].\n\nIn 2006 Lucas co-led a Beefheart tribute band, Fast 'n' Bulbous: the Captain Beefheart Project, which appeared at the Frankfurt Jazz Festival and the Jazz Em Agosto Festival in [[Lisbon]] during 2006. Their debut album ''Pork Chop Blue Around the Rind'' was profiled on NPR and charted on college radio in the United States. In Fall 2006, they toured Europe extensively, selling out shows at the London Jazz Festival, in Amsterdam's [[Bimhuis]], as well as playing in [[Bern]], Switzerland; [[Vienna]] and [[Schwaz]], Austria; and [[Ljubljana]], [[Slovenia]]. The group released its second album, ''Waxed Oop'', on [[Cuneiform Records]] in 2008.\n\nIn 2006, Lucas toured Europe with Phillip Johnston and five other jazz musicians as the Gary Lucas and Phillip Johnston Septet. The group performed jazz arrangements of Captain Beefheart's work in London, Amsterdam, Bern, Vienna, Schwaz (Austria) and Ljubljana.\n\n2017 marked the 50th anniversary of the release of Beefheart's album ''Safe as Milk,'' and saw Lucas engaged in numerous projects to mark the occasion. This included feature coverage in MOJO Magazine<ref>http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/mojo1711.jpg</ref> that coincided with the Captain Beefheart Weekend in Liverpool, England, where Lucas served on a panel at the participating Bluecoat Gallery. Lucas also collaborated with a group of Danish musicians for a Captain Beefheart tribute EP in 2017. In collaboration with Dutch DJ/producer Co de Cloet, the final interview given by Don Van Vliet was set to music composed by Lucas. Titled \"I Have a Cat,\" it was released on OkayMusic.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://soundcloud.com/garylucas/i-have-a-cat-excerpt-don-van-vliet-interview-w-co-de-kloet-music-by-gary-lucas | title=\"I Have a Cat\" excerpt--Don van Vliet interview w/ Co de Kloet set to music by Gary Lucas}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2017, the new Captain Beefheart tribute ensemble The World of Captain Beefheart, led by Lucas and Nona Hendryx, performed an album teaser performance at the Public Theater. The self-titled album was released in November 2017 on Knitting Factory Records.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/twocb/twocb.shtml | title=Gary Lucas - Official Website}}</ref> January 22, 2018 saw a special multimedia performance of The World of Captain Beefheart at City Winery NYC.\n\n==Collaborations==\nLucas first met Jeff Buckley in New York at the 1990 [[Tim Buckley]] tribute concert. Jeff Buckley stayed in New York and joined Lucas's band, Gods and Monsters. Lucas composed solo guitar instrumentals for \"Rise Up to Be\" and \"And You Will\", which later became the musical templates for \"Grace\" and \"Mojo Pin\",<ref name=\"garylucas.com\"/> which Lucas co-wrote with Buckley for his popular and critically acclaimed album ''[[Grace (Jeff Buckley album)|Grace]]''.<ref name=\"My Favourite Album\">{{cite web | url = http://www.abc.net.au/myfavouritealbum/top100.htm | title = My Favourite Album | accessdate = 2006-12-03 | date = 2006-12-03 | publisher = Australian Broadcasting Corporation}}</ref><ref>#1 Modern Rock Classic of all Time [[Mojo (magazine)]], 2006</ref> Early collaborations can also be heard on the Jeff Buckley and Gary Lucas album ''[[Songs to No One 1991\u20131992|Songs to No One]]'', which charted internationally with worldwide sales approaching 100,000. In the film ''Greetings from Tim Buckley''] (2013), [[Penn Badgely]] plays Buckley, and Tony Award winner Frank Wood plays Gary Lucas.  Emily Duff (her last name then was her maiden name) replaced Jeff Buckley as lead singer after he left to start his solo career.\n\nIn the mid-90s Lucas performed with [[Richard Barone]] in series of duo shows and live radio broadcasts in which Barone played [[Mellotron]]. Barone also guested on lead vocals with Lucas in his band [[Gods and Monsters (band)|Gods and Monsters]] and appears on subsequent albums.\n\nIn May 2011, Lucas released a new studio album with [[Gods and Monsters (band)|Gods and Monsters]], entitled ''The Ordeal of Civility''.<ref name=SDollar>{{cite news| url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052748703992704576305461484157844?mod=WSJ_LifeStyle_Lifestyle_5 | work=The Wall Street Journal | first=Steve | last=Dollar | title=Gods, Monsters and Guitars | date=May 5, 2011}}</ref> Gods and Monsters celebrated their 25th anniversary in June 2014 with a special performance at [[(Le) Poisson Rouge]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://the-guitar.com/gary-lucas-gods-and-monsters-25th-anniversary-concert/ |title=Gary Licas & Gods and Monsters 25th Anniversary Concert |date=June 28, 2014 |website=The-guitar.com |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref>\n\nIn 2003\u20132004 Lucas collaborated with Dutch lutist [[Jozef van Wissem]] on ''the Universe of Absence'' and ''Diplopia''. They have performed live on Dutch national TV together.\n\nIn 2007, Lucas collaborated on an album with underground electronic producer James R Hunter's project [[The Dark Poets]],  produced by British label manager [[Stevo Pearce]] of [[Some Bizzare Records]]. The album, ''Gary Lucas vs the Dark Poets \u2013 Beyond the Pale'', features an eclectic mixture of moody drum and bass, techno and rock tracks (notably \"Prime Time\", featuring vocals by Sarah Hilliard and James R. Hunter) as well as many early Lucas tracks and collaborations (including \"Procuress from Karmelitska Street\" featuring vocalist Pat Fulgoni of [[Kava Kava (band)|Kava Kava]] and original sketches of songs that went on to be used on Jeff Buckley's ''Grace'' album, including \"[[Grace (Jeff Buckley song)|Grace]]\" and \"[[Mojo Pin]]\").\n\nIn 2009, Lucas collaborated on a world music collaboration with Indian vocalist [[Najma Akhtar]]. Their album ''RISHTE'' combines rock, blues, folk, and [[raga]], on [[Harmonia Mundi]]/World Village. It was number 4 in the European World Music charts in 2009.<ref name=\"World Music Charts Europe\">{{cite web | url= http://www.wmce.de/?chartUrlMonth=9&chartUrlYear=2009 | title = World Music Charts Europe | accessdate = 2010-01-18 | publisher = [[European Broadcasting Union]]}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009, he collaborated with Juan Galeano on his album ''El Peregrino'', which debuted April 2010.\n\nIn 2010, Lucas collaborated with vocalist Dean Bowman on their \"spiritual roots project\" and gospel album, \"CHASE THE DEVIL\". The duo performed an amalgam of Hebrew and African American blues live in the United States and Europe.\n\nIn 2013 Lucas performed in several special collaborations in late 2013, including with Mother Falcon and [[Amanda Palmer]], with Richard Mader and Pat Fulgoni as the Ghosts of Prague at Jazz Dock, and with Toni Deszo, deBORT's lead saxophonist, at the Budapest Jazz Club.<ref name=\"garylucas.com\"/>\n\nIn 2013, Lucas performed with his 1930s Chinese pop project, the Edge of Heaven, in a sold-out show at the Fishman Space at BAM with vocalists Sally Kwok and Mo Hai Jing and his group Gods and Monsters.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lucas|first=Gary|title=Gary Lucas: Tour|url=http://garylucas.com/www/dates/|website=Garylucas.com|accessdate=2012-05-12}}</ref> The project was also performed as a trio featuring Lucas, Sally Kwok, and Mo Hai Jing at the 1930 Club in Shanghai. October also say Lucas performing in [[Federico Garc\u00eda Lorca]]'s \"La Casa de Bernarda Alba\" at the Gaia Arts Center in Havana.\n\nIn 2014, Lucas released an album called ''Otherworld'' on Esoteric Antenna. ''Otherworld'' is a collaborative effort with [[Peter Hammill]] of [[Van der Graaf Generator]].<ref name=\"guitarhoo\"/>\n\nIn 2014 ''Fleischerei: Music From Max Fleischer Cartoons,'' a collaboration between Lucas, [[Tony Award]]-nominee [[Sarah Stiles]], and Joe Fiedler, is a musical tribute to [[Max Fleischer]] and the jazz and swing scores that accompanied his animated work. Their public debut came at the [[Brooklyn Academy of Music]] Cafe in November 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wPxWjcwzWzk |title=Gary Lucas' Fleischerei: Music from Betty Boop at BAM cafe NYC |publisher=[[YouTube ]]|date=2014-11-16 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> The project features Stiles as [[Betty Boop]]. An album of the songs was released on February 5, 2015 on Cuneiform Records.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/fleischerei/fleischerei.shtml | title=Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015 Lucas's psychedelic world music trio, Pearly Clouds, released their debut album on Discovery Records on March 15, 2015.<ref name=\"pearlyclouds.com\">{{Cite web|url=http://pearlyclouds.com/|title=\u52b9\u679c\u691c\u8a3c\uff01DUO\u30af\u30ec\u30f3\u30b8\u30f3\u30b0\u30d0\u30fc\u30e0\u30af\u30ea\u30a2\u3067\u6bdb\u7a74\u306f\u7121\u304f\u306a\u308b\uff1f26\u6b73\u306e\u9854\u51fa\u3057\u53e3\u30b3\u30df|website=Pearlyclouds.com}}</ref> The project features Hungarian traditional folk vocalist Enik\u0151 Szab\u00f3 and Serbian saxophonist Toni Dezso.\n\nLucas traveled to England in February 2017 to produce a new album from [[Ed Laurie]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.garylucas.com/photos.shtml |title = Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref> Lucas's celebrated album ''Rishte'' with Najma Akhtar was reissued on OkayMusic, rising to #4 on the World Music Charts Europe.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/ng/ |title = Gary Lucas :: Najma Akhtar and Gary Lucas|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref> Fall 2017 saw the release of the album \"Gary and Toni Go Nutz!\", a duo recording of songs and improvisation by Lucas and Toni Dezso of Pearly Clouds, on Rare Lumiere and Okay Records. Rokus Kalapis created an animated feature to accompany the album.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MI8WqmgvIP0|title=CYBERPUNK - music by Gary Lucas and T\u00f3ni Dezs\u0151, visuals by R\u00f3kus Kalapis|publisher=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n\nLucas began working on a follow-up to his celebrated album ''The Edge of Heaven'' with vocalist Feifei Yang and saxophonist Jason Candler<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://soundcloud.com/garylucas/a-tale-of-the-mah-jong-game-gary-lucas-w-feifei-yang-and-jason-candler |title = \"A Tale of the Mah-Jong Game\"-Gary Lucas, Feifei Yang & Jason Candler|website=Soundcloud.com}}</ref> in late 2017, including a version of Lucas and Buckley's \"Grace.\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://vimeo.com/243361252 | title=\"GRACE\" in MANDARIN--GARY LUCAS, FEIFEI YANG and JASON CANDLER @ 2017 NYC JEFF BUCKLEY TRIBUTE|website=Vimeo.com| date=2017-11-17}}</ref> At the annual Moon Festival, at Lincoln Center's Alice Tully Hall, Lucas and Yang performed with the 70-piece Asian Cultural Orchestra, including the debut of their duet of \"The Moon Represents My Heart.\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://vimeo.com/244536918 | title=Feifei Yang and Gary Lucas Live at the Moon Festival NYC 9/15/17--\"The Moon Represents My Heart\"| date=2017-11-26}}</ref> In celebration of the Chinese New Year in February 2018, the new Edge of Heaven trio performed at the Laurie Beechman Theatre.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/edgelive/edgelive.shtml | title=Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://vimeo.com/258619596 | title=\"GRACE\" --GARY LUCAS&#039; THE EDGE OF HEAVEN LIVE @ the Laurie Beechman Theatre NYC 2/16/18 Chinese New Year| date=2018-03-05}}</ref> Yang and Lucas also served as judges on CCTV's \"Super Baby\" talent competition and a documentary about their collaborations is forthcoming on SinoVision.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://vimeo.com/249453847 | title=Gary Lucas & Feifei Yang after judging CCTV&#039;s new talent show \"Super Baby\" 12/16/17| date=2018-01-02}}</ref>\n\nEarly in 2018, Lucas performed his Buckley tribute \"Touched by Grace\" with Jolene Grunberg in Amsterdam.\n\n==Solo projects==\n[[File:Gary Lucas at UN.jpeg|thumbnail|right|Gary Lucas performs before the General Assembly of the United Nations on International Holocaust Remembrance Day, January 27, 2017.Photo by Jason Candler]]\nDuring his fourth tour of Russia in 2005, Lucas performed his original solo guitar adaptation of the Lucas/Horn score accompanying the silent classic German horror film ''[[The Golem: How He Came into the World|The Golem]]'' (1920) in Moscow and Saint Petersburg and appeared on national TV before an estimated 50 million viewers, as well as being feted in the Russian edition of ''[[Rolling Stone]]''. He's played with ''The Golem'' solo globally since the live debut of the duet score he and keyboardist Walter Horn wrote for the movie in 1989 for the [[Brooklyn Academy of Music]] Next Wave Festival. He has performed it at the [[Venice Biennale]], London's [[Royal Festival Hall]], the New York Jewish Film Festival at [[Lincoln Center]], as part of a weeklong artist-in-residency at the [[Quebec City Summer Festival]], at the ''Alien'' artist [[H. R. Giger]]'s Retrospective in Prague (home of the Golem), at Atlanta's [[Dragon Con]] 2002, the largest science fiction festival in the world, and at the fifth annual [[Pop Montreal]] music and film festival.\n\nOther recent concert appearances include a concert at the Czech Embassy in Washington, D.C., by invitation of the Czech ambassador spotlighting Lucas's solo guitar arrangements of Czech classical music in honor of the 14th anniversary of the [[Velvet Revolution]].\n\nGary Lucas's January 2012 solo tour of Europe began in Spain with a program on National Basque Radio Euskadi, and a performance of the \"Spanish Dracula for Bilbao's Musiketan Festival\" in Sala BBK. In England, Lucas conducted his Captain Beefheart Symposium two nights in a row at Liverpool's Philharmonic and record 8 tracks in a collaboration with [[Bryan Ferry]] at Olympia Studios.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lucas|first=Gary|title=Captain Beefheart Symposium|url=http://garylucas.com/www/capt/|website=Garylucas.com|accessdate=2012-05-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Towie|first=Steve|title=Review: Captain Beefheart Symposium|url=http://www.sevenstreets.com/music-and-listening/review-captain-beefheart-symposium/|accessdate=2012-05-12|newspaper=Seven Streets|date=2012-01-21}}</ref> Two solo performances followed in [[Lisbon]] and [[Porto]], Portugal, with guest performer Diana Silviera.<ref>{{cite web|author=Alexandre Elias |url=https://www.dn.pt/inicio/artes/interior.aspx?content_id=2266284&seccao=M%FAsica |title=Concerto - Gary Lucas, um her\u00f3i da guitarra, ao vivo na ZDB - M\u00fasica - DN |website=Dn.pt |date=2012-01-27 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://issuu.com/metro_portugal/docs/20120127_pt_lisbon |title=20120127_pt_lisbon by metro portugal |website=Issuu.com |date= |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> The tour finished in Paris with a surprise performance at La Feline, and solo show at the New Morning with Cheyenne Schiavone, Beatrice Demi-Mondaine, Jean-Francis Pauvros, and Daniel Yvinec,<ref>{{cite web|last=Lucas|first=Gary|title=Solo and Acoustic Shows|url=http://www.garylucas.com/solo.shtml|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref> reviewed favorably by E. Corvee, 12 February 2012, in [[Politis (France)|''Politis'']]''.''<ref>{{cite news|last=Corvee|first=Elodie|title=je ne rentre dans aucune categorie|url=http://www.politis.fr/Gary-Lucas-Je-ne-rentre-dans,17002.html|accessdate=2012-05-12|newspaper=Politis|date=2012-02-01}}</ref>\n\nLucas returned to Europe for a debut solo in [[Sardinia]] at the Santa Arresi Jazz Festival, and a special concert at the [[Paradiso (Amsterdam)|Paradiso]] in Amsterdam on September 2, 2012, in a collaboration with the [[Metropole Orkest]] and Dutch singers entitled \"The music of Jeff Buckley and Gary Lucas\" and featuring Italian vocalist Alessio Franchini;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Wpxf3GhGXpg |title=Gary Lucas & Metropole Orchestra - Mojo Pin - Amsterdam 09-02 2012 |publisher=[[YouTube]] |date=2012-09-03 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> this coincided with publication of his first book, ''Touched by Grace\u2014La Mia Musica con Jeff Buckley''. He then performed a week of shows in the Czech Republic, headlining Prague's Alternativa Festival<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alternativa-festival.cz/detail-en/gary-lucas-j-h-michal-nejtek |title=Alternativa 2015: 23rd issue of music festival. 7\u201414/11 Prague |website=Alternativa-festival.cz |date= |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> solo, appearing live for three hours of interviews and performance on national Beat Radio, performing in [[Jablonec nad Nisou|Jablonec]], [[Bohemia]], with his \"Monsters from the Id\" music and film project.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/id/ |title=monsters from the id |website=Garylucas.com |date=2006-10-28 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> He also performed at [[Shakespeare and Company (bookstore)|Shakespeare and Company]], the legendary [[Paris]] bookstore.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://united-mutations.blogspot.com/2012/10/gary-lucas-at-durango-film-festival.html |title=United Mutations: GARY LUCAS AT THE DURANGO FILM FESTIVAL 2012 10 19 |website=United-mutations.blogspot.com |date=2012-10-14 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref>\n\n''Fleischerei'' was performed throughout 2016 at the Jewish Film Festival in Washington, D.C., the Porgy and Bess Jazz Club in Wien, the Boston Jewish Film Festival, the City Winery NYC and City Winery Chicago seders, as well as at the City Winery NYC klemzer brunch.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n\nLucas headlined the Pisa Internet Festival<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.internetfestival.it/en/ |title = Home - IF2019}}</ref> with a solo acoustic concert at Teatro Lumiere. He also performed with guest vocalist Danae Villanueva Blanco at the Gaia Arts Center Havana Cuba in May 2016.<ref>http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/granma5-13-16.jpg</ref> In December 2016, Lucas reunited with members of Plastic People of the Universe, DG 307, and Urfaust at the Blues Bahnof Prague.\n\nOn October 1, 2016, Lucas performed an acoustic solo concert to close the Jewish Museume of Vienna's exhibition \"Stars of David.\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://vimeo.com/188006251 | title=Gary Lucas Live at the Jewish Museum of Vienna 10/1/16 \"Stars of David\" Concert| date=2016-10-19}}</ref>\n\nFor Holocaust Remembrance Day 2017, Lucas performed solo before the General Assembly of the United Nations.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://vimeo.com/201390227 | title=Jan.27.17 Holocaust Memorial Ceremony GUITARIST GARY LUCAS (1)| date=2017-01-28}}</ref>\n\nA solo tour of Europe in 2017 also saw Lucas perform in Czech director Pavel Gobl's forthcoming ''The Supervision of the Interpretation of Dreams,'' as well as performances at the Varnsdorf State Theater and the Danish National Library. Lucas was honored to celebrate the 150th show at Pori, Finland's underground club Validi Karkia.<ref name=\"youtube1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aoeVyJZCSjo|title=Gary Lucas & Miryam LaTrece \"In The Cantina\" a Jeff Buckley Tribute -Recoletos Jazz-|publisher=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Lucas was featured in a two-part special on Co de Kloet's \"Co Live\" program on Dutch radio NPO, looking back over Gary's career.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://soundcloud.com/garylucas/colive-gary-lucas-special-on-npo-radio-2-part-one |title = CoLive! Gary Lucas Special on NPO Radio 2 part one|website=Soundcloud.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://soundcloud.com/garylucas/colive-gary-lucas-special-on-npo-radio-2-part-two |title = CoLive! Gary Lucas Special on NPO Radio 2 part two|website=Soundecloud.com}}</ref>\n\n2018 will see Lucas embark on a solo tour of multi-media performances titled \u201cAn Evening with Gary Lucas: From Beefheart to Buckley and Beyond,\u201d including 12 dates in [http://garylucas.com/www/dates/UK_Tour_2018.jpg May 2018 in the UK]<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/fbbb/fbbb.shtml |title = Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref><ref>http://garylucas.com/www/dates/UK_Tour_2018.jpg</ref>\n\n==Tribute performances==\n[[File:Gary Lucas performing.jpg|thumbnail|right|Gary Lucas performing \"The Music of Jeff Buckley and Gary Lucas\" with The Metropole Orchestra at Paradiso Amsterdam on September 2, 2012. Photo: Sjaniek Schaap]]\nLucas returned to New York City to play with the [[Les Paul Trio]] and singer [[Jann Klose]] in NYC's Iridium Jazz Club, with high-profile solo appearances at [[(Le) Poisson Rouge]] and [[Joe's Pub]] with [[M'Lumbo]] as well as on their new release ''Popular Science'', and headlining a tribute to avant-garde band [[The Shaggs]] at [[The Bellhouse]] in Brooklyn, where he performed with Gods and Monsters. The year wrapped with a trip to Havana\u2014Lucas' fifth appearance there\u2014where he performed three nights at the Gaia Arts Center in a tribute to [[Michelangelo Antonioni]] on the occasion of his 100th anniversary; performed live on national [[Radio Havana]] and [[Radio Ta\u00edno]]; and was interviewed and filmed performing live by national Austrian television ORF for a program which aired 2013.\n\nAdditional touring in 2013 included special performances focused on well-known collaborators [[Jeff Buckley]] and [[Captain Beefheart]]. Lucas performed a tribute concert to Buckley at the Barezzi Festival in [[Parma]], Italy, with Vinicio Caposella and Alessio Franchini, where he was also presented with a Lifetime Achievement Award. Lucas performed with the Metropole Orkest at the Paradiso in Amsterdam as part of \"The World of Captain Beefheart\", a tribute to Captain Beefheart (Don Van Vliet), that also featured [[Nona Hendryx]], Jolene Grunberg, and Tom Trapp.\n\nLucas returned to Italy in Summer 2015, performing across the country with Italian singer/songwriter Alessio Franchini, including as part of Franchini's ''Touch of Grace'' Tribute to Jeff Buckley at the Teatro della Luna in Milan, as well as an appearance at Italian singer-songwriter Vinicio Caposella's \"Moon in June Festival\" in Umbria.<ref>[http://www.lastampa.it/2015/03/19/multimedia/spettacoli/lucas-cos-ho-scritto-grace-con-jeff-buckley-8HmFj65dDfAmoM74hkD1VO/pagina.html] {{dead link|date=January 2020}}</ref><ref>http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/larepubjbt.jpg</ref>\n\nIn 2015 Lucas led Gods and Monsters as Music Director of ''A State of Grace'', a multi-artist tribute to both Tim and Jeff Buckley.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.stateofgracelive.com |title = Mystic Forest Shower Curtain Sets,Hand Knotted Area Rug,Cute White Food Pillow Perfect Cushion}}</ref> The tribute saw Gary perform with singer/songwriter [[Martha Wainwright]], [[Steve Kilbey]] (of [[The Church (band)]]), and other vocalists over 6 nights in Sydney, Melbourne, Canberra and at the Brisbane Festival.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://themusic.com.au/music/livereviews/2015/09/29/a-state-of-grace-enmore-theatre-luke-saunders/ |title = /}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2012, Lucas performed live before an estimated viewing audience of 70 million [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EzUDjINbgfs on CNBC] in a segment devoted to Gibson Guitars; later that summer the national French ARTE Channel interviewed him for the documentary [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m1-k-7v634I \"Rock Attitude\"]. He was also interviewed and filmed performing live by National Austrian Television ORF for a program which will air in 2013.\n\nAt the [[Peace Hotel]] in November 2016, Lucas and collaborator Sally Kwok performed a tribute Chinese pop of the 1930s. Later that month, Lucas performed as part of the \"Hendrix in Harlem\" Tribute at the Apollo Theater, alongside Fishbone, Nona Hendryx, and Ernie Isley.\n\n2017 saw Lucas pay tribute to Buckley over two nights at Recoletos Jazz Club in Madrid alongside Mercedes Ferrer and Miryam Latrece.<ref name=\"youtube1\"/> In September, Lucas performed a sold-out tribute to Buckley in London with special guest Mari Conti.<ref>[https://continuouscruiser.com/2017/11/23/when-gary-lucas-met-jeff-buckley/] {{dead link|date=January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Lectures, classes, symposia==\nLucas has spoken widely on his life and career. He also lectures widely on the mechanics of songwriting, extensive collaborations, composing for film, and the music business at the Amsterdam Music Conservatorum, [[Yale University]] (his alma mater), the [[University of Hawaii]], [[New York University]], and [[Columbia University]]. He has given guitar master classes since the late 1990s at such institutions as the Amsterdam Music Conservatory and in Honolulu at the [[University of Hawaii]]. He has also lectured at [[Rogers State University]] in Oklahoma, and [[McGill University]] in Montreal, Canada. In 2013, Lucas gave a [[TEDx]] talked titled \"Blues and the Tuning of the World.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TsfkHolImNE|title=Blues and the Tuning of the World: Gary Lucas at TEDxBergenCommunityCollege|publisher=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n\nIn Fall 2012, Lucas gave a masterclass and a concert in Paris with French guitarist David Konopnicki and his band at the Henri Dutilleux Music Conservatoire. In April 2014, Lucas gave a masterclass at Rutgers University Mason Gross School of the Arts, with students noting that \"his guitar playing and compositions were unlike anything else I have heard before\" and that \"he has some great ideas about life and music.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/mclass/ |title=masterclass |website=Garylucas.com|date=2013-01-03 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> December 2016 saw Lucas giving a Guitar Masterclass alongside a seminar on songwriting at [[Conservatorium van Amsterdam]]. Lucas has also given masterclasses at the [[School of Jazz at the New School]].\n\nWhile touring Mexico in 2014, Lucas was invited by the United States Ambassador to Mexico [[Earl Anthony Wayne]] to perform a concert at the Benjamin Franklin Library in [[Mexico City]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/bio/ |title=Official Website|website=Garylucas.com |date= |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> as part of the ambassador's outreach program for disadvantaged youth. Following the performance, Lucas received an official letter of endorsement and appreciation from Ambassador Wayne.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/mclass/mexico_letter1412.pdf |title=Letter from Embassy of the United States of America, Mexico |website=Garylucas.com |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> Lucas returned to perform again in December 2015 and November 2016, both at the invitation of the U.S. ambassador.\n\nLucas has continually conducted a popular symposium on his former mentor and collaborator, Captain Beefheart (Don Van Vliet), both in the U.S. and in Europe. The symposium focuses not only on Van Vliet's music, but also his work as a visual artist. Lucas discusses the history of Vliet's band, collaborations, personality, and techniques in addition to sharing archival footage and unreleased music.<ref name=\"http://garylucas.com/www/capt\">{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/capt/ |title=captain beefheart symposium |website=Garylucas.com |date=2010-12-19 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> His two symposia in Liverpool in January 2012 were sold out. He presented at the Zappanale in Bad Doberan, Germany in August 2012, followed by a reunion of jazz-rock Beefheart tribute ensemble Fast 'N' Bulbous co-led by Phillip Johnston.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lucas|first=Gary|title=Captain Beefheart Symposium Page|url=http://garylucas.com/www/capt/|website=Garylucas.com|accessdate=2012-05-05}}</ref>\n\nThe symposium has been given at numerous venues, including the [[Knitting Factory]] in Brooklyn, the Independent in San Francisco, [[Echoplex (venue)|Echoplex]] in Los Angeles, and Casa Del Lago in Mexico City, and often features notable guests, which have previously included Matt Groening, Robert Williams, Terry Van Vliet, Francis McCarthy, Gary Marker, Kristine McKenna, Bill Moseley, and many others.<ref name=\"http://garylucas.com/www/capt\"/>\n\nLucas was named Artist in Residence at Royal Liverpool Philharmonic Hall in Liverpool England in December, 2015.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://czb.ro/articol/10263/ |title = Articol: Gary Lucas is Artist in Residence at Royal Liverpool Philharmonic Hall - Revista de Muzica Online: ClickZoomBytes - CZB.ro}}</ref> During this residency, Lucas performed numerous solo works and presented his new Jeff Buckley Symposium.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/jbs/jbs.shtml |title = Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref>\n\n==Film and television scores==\nLucas has composed and performed live accompaniment for several films throughout his career,<ref name=\"garylucas1\">{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/film/ |title=live music and film projects |website=Garylucas.com |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> the first having been a score to the 1920 silent film ''[[The Golem: How He Came into the World]]'', composed with Walter Horn and debuted in 1989 at the [[Brooklyn Academy of Music]] Next Wave Festival. Since that premiere, a solo, guitar version of the accompaniment to ''The Golem'' has been performed at numerous venues and festivals around the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/golem/ |title=the golem |website=Garylucas.com |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> He has gone on to compose live guitar accompaniments for several films, sometimes in collaboration with other artists.<ref name=\"garylucas1\"/>\n\nThroughout 2013, Lucas extensively toured his live film accompaniments. His long-running live score to George Melford's ''[[Dr\u00e1cula (1931 Spanish-language film)|Dr\u00e1cula]]'' was performed at the [[Jerusalem Film Festival]], the Silent Movie Theatre in Hollywood, the Cineteca Nacional in Mexico City, the [[United Palace]] Theatre in Harlem, Kino Aero in [[Prague]], and Kino Siska in [[Slovenia]].<ref name=\"garylucas.com\">{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/bio/ |title=biography |website=Garylucas.com |date=2013-10-05 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> Lucas's live score to [[Jos\u00e9 Mojica Marins]]' \"Esta Noite Encarnerei no teu Cadaver\" saw its European debut at the [[Melkweg]] in Amsterdam in May 2013.<ref name=\"garylucas.com\"/>\n\nLucas has continued to perform his live film accompaniments, including ''Monsters of the Id'' at [[Monsterpalooza]] in Burbank, and ''This Night I will Possess Your Corpse'' at the [[Wexner Center for the Arts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wexarts.org/performing-arts/esta-noite-encarnarei-no-teu-cadaver-night-i-will-possess-your-corpse |title=Esta Noite Encarnarei no Teu Cadaver (This Night I Will Possess your Corpse) &#124; Wexner Center for the Arts |website=Wexarts.org |date=2014-03-01 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> He also premiered live accompaniment to the 1934 silent, Chinese film ''[[The Goddess (1934 film)|The Goddess]]'' in early 2014. Fall of 2014 saw the premiere of new live scores to ''[[Frankenstein (1931 film)|Frankenstein]]'' and ''[[Vampyr]]''.\n\nIn Fall 2009, Gary Lucas debuted his new live program of solo guitar arrangements of famous film music at the 5th [[Jecheon International Music & Film Festival]] in [[South Korea]]. He was also invited by the Festival Internacional del Nuevo Cine Latinoamerica to preview his score for the Spanish version of ''Dracula'' (1931) at the 31st [[Havana Film Festival]] in Havana, Cuba.<ref name=\"Gary Lucas Under the Skin of Dracula\">{{cite web | url= http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/Granma_Dec09.pdf | title = Gary Lucas Under the Skin of Dracula\" (English trans. of article in Spanish, \"Lucas bajo la piel de Dracula\" in the Havana newspaper ''Granma Culturales'', 12/14/09.)| accessdate = 2010-01-18|publisher=[[Granma (newspaper)|Granma]]}}</ref> Lucas performs the European premiere of his Spanish \"Dracula\" project at the 9th [[Transylvania International Film Festival]] in [[Cluj-Napoca]], Romania, on May 30, 2010, in the open-air outside the Banfi Botzida Castle.\n\nLucas returned to Cuba in December 2010 for the 32nd [[Havana Film Festival]], and debuted a new live score accompanying a Brazilian horror classic, ''Esta Noite Encarnerei no teu Cadaver'' (\"Tonight I will Possess Your Corpse\").<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.habanafilmfestival.com/noticias/index.php?newsid=469 |title=Festival Internacional del Nuevo Cine Latinoamericano |language=es |website=Habanafilmfestival.com |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Gary performed his live solo score to [[The Goddess (1934 film)]], originally premiered at Foundation Botin in Santander, Spain, at [[Pioneer Works]] in Red Hook Brooklyn.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/goddess/goddess.shtml |title = Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref> His live accompaniment to ''[[The Exterminating Angel]]'', which premiered at the Havana Film Festival in 2011, was also debuted in the United States at Pioneer Works.\n\n2017 saw the premiere at Roulette in Brooklyn of Gary's new live score for [[Orson Welles]]' 1938 silent classic ''Too Much Johnson.''<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/tmj/tmj.shtml |title = Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref> A new film score set to a fragment of the Russian futurist avant-garde short ''Shackled By Film'' (starring [[Vladimir Mayakovsky]] and [[Lilya Brik]] was premiered at [[Emir Kusturica]]'s [[Kustendorf International Film Festival]] in January 2018. In February 2018, Lucas returned to Roulette to premiere a new live film score to a collection of short films by visionary film director [[Curtis Harrington]]<ref name=\"ReferenceB\">{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/www/harrington/harrington.shtml |title = Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref>\n* ''[[The Golem: How He Came into the World]]'' with Walter Horn.\n* ''[[The Unholy Three (1925 film)|The Unholy Three]]'', commissioned by [[Film Society of Lincoln Center]]).\n* ''[[J'accuse! (1938 film)|J'accuse]]'' with Dutch-Iranian composer Reza Namavar, commissioned by the Netherlands Holland Festival.\n* ''[[The Exterminating Angel]]''\n* ''[[Dr\u00e1cula (1931 Spanish-language film)|Dracula]]'', the score Lucas has toured most frequently, having been performed at several film and music festivals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/dracula/ |title=spanish-language \"dracula\" |website=Garylucas.com |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref>\n* ''[[This Night I'll Possess Your Corpse]]''\n* ''[[The Goddess (1934 film)|The Goddess]]'' debuted at Fundaci\u00f3n Bot\u00edn in January 2014 as part of the \"Golden Age of Chinese Cinema\" series curated by [[Film Society of Lincoln Center]] Director Emeritus Richard Pena.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/goddess/ |title=The Goddess |website=Garylucas.com|date=2014-01-08 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref>\n* ''[[Vampyr]]'' was premiered at [[AFI Silver]] in fall of 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/vampyr/ |title=Vampyr |website=Garylucas.com |date=2014-11-01 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref>\n* ''[[Frankenstein (1931 film)|Frankenstein]]'' premiered at [[United Palace]] on Halloween 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/fstein/ |title=Frankenstein |website=Garylucas.com |date=2014-10-31 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref>\n* ''Cinefantastique'' (solo guitar arrangements of famous film music), named one of the Top 10 Roots Albums of 2013 by the Philadelphia City Paper<ref name=\"citypaper.net\">{{cite web|author= |url=http://citypaper.net/article.php?Top-10-roots-albums-of-2013-18224 |title=Top 10 roots albums of 2013 :: Cover :: Philadelphia City Paper |website=Citypaper.net |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> and Best Guitar Album of the year by Gapplegate Guitar and Bass Blog.<ref name=\"citypaper.net\"/>\n* ''[[Too Much Johnson]] premiered at Roulette Intermedium Brooklin in January 2017\n* ''The Short Films of Curtis Harrington'', a collection of short films accompanied by a live score by Lucas, premiered in February 2017 at Roulette Intermedium Brooklyn.<ref name=\"ReferenceB\"/>\n* ''American Faust: From Condi to Neo-Condi'' an award-winning documentary on [[Condoleezza Rice]], directed by [[Sebastian Doggart]], additional scoring\n* ''Trust Me'' (a [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]] documentary, original score)\n* ''Bed and Breakfast 9/11'' (an award-winning documentary shown on [[PBS]])\n* ''The Legacy of [[Jedwabne]]'' (documentary by [[S\u0142awomir Gr\u00fcnberg]])\n* ''[[LaLee's Kin: The Legacy of Cotton]]'' (an [[oscar nomination|Oscar-nominated]] [[Maysles Films]] documentary for [[HBO]], screened at the [[Museum of Modern Art]] in New York as part of their Maysles Films 50 Year Retrospective; [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] wrote: \"Gary Lucas' [[Delta blues]] guitar music adds vivid color to this report from America's forgotten underbelly\")\n* ''Dragon Boys'' (Canadian \"movie of the week\") 2007.\n* ''For Love and Honor'' (Erik Greenberg Anjou's documentary about American Ivy League collegiate football).\n* ''American Faust: From Condi to Neo-Condi'' (score, 2010)\n* In the early 2000s, Lucas performed a guitar rendition of the theme music to [[BBC1]] soap opera ''[[EastEnders]]''.\n* \"Farewell Angelina\" as performed by Lucas and [[Jeff Buckley]] was featured on [[Roadies (TV series)]].\n\n==Awards and honors==\n\nLucas was the subject of Klaus Totzler's [[documentary]] ''Gary Lucas in Havana'', which aired on Austrian national television ORF and on 3SAT TV in May 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NcwX-lKII6g |title=Gary Lucas on 3sat mediathek Austrian TV |publisher=[[YouTube]] |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref>\n\nIn the last few years Lucas has been profiled in the ''[[International Herald Tribune]]'', ''Lib\u00e9ration'', and featured on the cover of ''[[The Forward]]'' as well as the national Dutch newspaper ''[[Het Parool]]''. According to the Beefheart website: \"Since the end of the Magic Band, he has been very prolific in his own right, solo and within a band, releasing almost an album a year since 1991. His virtuoso solo live shows are awesome in the sounds he extracts from his guitar.\"<ref name=\"beefheart\" />\n\nIn 2009, [[Classic Rock (magazine)|''Classic Rock'']] named Lucas one of the \"100 Greatest Living Guitarists\".<ref>Classic Rock magazine, August 2009.</ref> In October 2013, Lucas received a Lifetime Achievement Award at the Barezzi Festival in Parma, Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://czb.ro/articol/6004/ |title=Articol: Gary Lucas in Paris, Bristol, London, Aberdeen, Edinburgh, Cork, Dublin, Mexico City, Prague, Budapest and Beyond - Revista De Muzica Online: ClickZoomBytes |website=Czb.ro |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> Lucas was given an Acker Award for Achievement in Avant Garde Music in June 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ackerawards.com/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140603192737/http://www.ackerawards.com/#!nyc-awards/canh|url-status=dead|title=\u30d5\u30ec\u30a4\u30a2\u30af\u30ea\u30cb\u30c3\u30af\u6a2a\u6d5c\u9662\u306e\u8a55\u5224\u3068\u53e3\u30b3\u30df\u304c\u30a2\u30a6\u30c8\u3002\u6599\u91d1\u3068\u4e88\u7d04|archivedate=June 3, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe U.S. Consul General of [[Milan]], [[Philip T. Reeker]], presented Lucas with the Consul General's Award for [[Cultural Diplomacy]] on March 21, 2015, following a special performance and reception at U.S. Consulate in Milan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/pr/pr_latest.html |title=Official Website |website=Garylucas.com |date=2015-10-25 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/grfx/consulate1503.jpg |format=JPG |title=Letter from Consulate General of the United States of America |website=Garylucas.com |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref>\n\nLucas received the Lifetime Achievement Award at the Premio Ciampi Festival in Tuscany, named for legendary Italian songwriter [[Piero Ciampi]], in December 2015.\n\nConsultant for ''[[Greetings from Tim Buckley]]'' about Jeff Buckley's early days working in NYC, directed by Dan Algrant and starring Penn Badgley (\"Gossip Girl\") as Jeff. Character of Gary Lucas played by Tony Award-winning actor Frank Wood. Lucas plays his own guitar parts for the film. The film was released worldwide in cinemas in 2013.<ref>{{cite news|last=Dickey|first=Josh L.|title=Frank Wood Aboard 'Buckley' |url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1118041626|publisher=Variety|accessdate=2012-05-01|date=2011-08-22}}</ref>\n\n==Writing==\n2013 saw the publishing of Lucas's book ''Touched by Grace: My Time with Jeff Buckley'' published in English by Jawbone Press.<ref name=\"jawbonepress.com\">{{cite web|url=http://jawbonepress.com/touched-by-grace/ |title=JAWBONE &#124; smart books for musical minds |website=Jawbonepress.com |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> In support of this, Lucas performed a string of shows in the United Kingdom, as well as two performances and signings at [[Shakespeare and Company (bookstore)|Shakespeare and Company]] in Paris.\n\nArcana Books (Italy) published Gary Lucas' book, ''Touched by Grace\u2014La Mia Musica con Jeff Buckley'', in September 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/tbg/ |title=touched by grace |website=Garylucas.com |date= |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> [http://www.elisarusso.com/gary-lucas-touched-by-grace-la-mia-musica-con-jeff-buckley-arcana/ The book received excellent reviews in the Italian press]. Publication was supported with several Italian in store appearances and concerts by Lucas, including Feltrinelli in [[Trieste]], the [[Fnac]] Megastore in Milan, and the Madame Guitar Festival in [[Tricesimo]] (Lucas' third appearance there). ''Touched by Grace'' was published in English by Jawbone Press in October 2013.<ref name=\"jawbonepress.com\"/> [[Mojo (magazine)|''Mojo'']] gave the book four stars.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/mojo1311.jpg |title=Touched By Grace : My Time With Jeff Buckley |author=Gary Lucas |website=Garylucas.com |accessdate=2014-07-12}}</ref> Roy Trakin of [[Hits (magazine)|''Hits'' (magazine)]] named the book among his top 10 of 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://addictedtonoise.com.au/roy-trakins-best-2014/ |title=Roy Trakin's Best of 2014 - Exiled Off Main Street - International Roots Music - Exiled Off Main Street \u2013 International Roots Music |website=Addictedtonoise.com.au |date=2014-12-17 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref>\n\nLucas has written extensively, working in poetry and fiction, as well as reflections on music and his own experiences.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://garylucas.com/writings.shtml |title = Gary Lucas - Official Website|website=Garylucas.com}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nLucas draws from the [[blues]] tradition and includes styles such as [[psychedelic rock]], [[world music]], and [[jazz]], as well as [[classical music|classical]] works. ''[[The New York Times]]'' described his guitar playing: \"Gary Lucas plays guitar the way [[Salvador Dal\u00ed]] painted, with dazzling displays of technique, wicked humor, and a thirst to completely refashion his art from its basic elements\".<ref>New York Times, November 2000.</ref>\n\nLucas has been described as a \"guitarist with a global guitar\" (Larry Rohter, 9 May 2011, ''New York Times'') \"one of the best and most original guitarists in America\" (David Fricke, 16 November 2006, ''[[Rolling Stone]]''); a \"legendary leftfield guitarist\" (''[[The Guardian]]'', 24 December 2005); \"the thinking man's guitar hero\" (''[[The New Yorker]]'', 8 January 2007), \"perhaps the greatest living electric guitar player\" ([[Daniel Levitin]]) and one of \"the most innovative and challenging guitarists playing today\" (''[[fRoots]]'', March 2002). Lucas' style melds easily into rock and blues, has \"avant-garde affinities\", but is \"not easily typecast\" according to the [[The Wall Street Journal|''Wall Street Journal'']].<ref name=\"SDollar\" />\n\nLucas has collaborated intermittently with DJ Cosmo (Colleen Murphy) as Wild Rumpus. Having worked together in the Manhattan [[rave]] scene, their work focuses on incorporating Lucas's [[electric guitar]] work and various other genre influences into [[electronic dance music]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/wildr/ |title=Wild Rumpus |website=Garylucas.com |date= |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> In 2014 the duo released the double-vinyl album ''Musical Blaze-up'' on Bitches Brew. Curious Animal gave the LP a seven out of ten, saying \"the international sound is the album's&nbsp;... big defining feature\".<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.curiousanimal.com/album-review-musical-blaze-up-by-wild-rumpus/ |title=Album Review: Musical Blaze-Up by Wild Rumpus - Curious Animal Magazine |website=Curiousanimal.com |date=2014-06-02 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> I House U called ''Musical Blaze-Up'' a \"rawkus musical [[mashup (music)|mash-up]]\" and the video for lead single \"Rock the Joint\" was named BBC 6 Music Video of the Week.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://acloserlisten.com/2014/04/02/spring-music-preview-part-ii/ |title=Spring Music Preview Part II |website=Acloserlisten.com |date=2014-04-02 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref>\n\nFebruary 2014 saw the release of ''Otherworld'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/oworld/ |title=Otherworld: Peter Hammill and |website=Garylucas.com |date=2014-04-13 |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref> an experimental collaboration between Lucas and [[Peter Hammill]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Thom Jurek |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/other-world-mw0002604043 |title=Other World - Peter Hammill,Gary Lucas &#124; Songs, Reviews, Credits, Awards |website=[[AllMusic]] |date=2014-02-03 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> The album was well received by critics, with ''MAX Magazine Italy'' writing, \"Guitars, abstract landscapes, breathtaking texts (as always when a true poet as Hammill gathers in the field), spectral songs, layers, all conspire to create something unexpectedly powerful and disarming\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/rvw_14.html#MAX1401 |title=reviews |website=Garylucas.com |date=2014-04-25 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> Lucas and Hammill were featured on the covers of ''Guitar Player'' magazine<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/gp1405.pdf |title=Guitar Player magazine article |website=Garylucas.com |accessdate=2014-07-12}}</ref> and ''Rock Society'' magazine<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/rs-cover1403.jpg |title=Rock Society magazine article |website=Garylucas.com |accessdate=2014-07-12}}</ref> for the project, in addition to featured coverage in ''Prog'' magazine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/prog1402.pdf |quote=He was the best live artist I saw when I first came to London in '73. He really made an impression on me |title=Lucas on Hammill : The Odd Couple |website=Garylucas.com |accessdate=2014-07-12}}</ref> ''[[Record Collector]]'' gave the album four stars (out of four),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://recordcollectormag.com/reviews/other-world |title=Other World - Record Collector Magazine |website=Recordcollectormag.com |date=2011-05-26 |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref> and [[Uncut (magazine)|''Uncut'']] marked it seven out of ten.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/uncut1404.jpg |title=Peter Hammill / Gary Lucas : Other World : Esoteric Antenna |website=Garylucas.com |accessdate=2014-07-12}}</ref> In support of the collaboration, Lucas and Hammill performed together at the Gouveia Art Rock Festival in Portugal and at the [[Teatro de la Ciudad]] in Mexico City.\n\n''The Edge of Heaven'', is an album of Lucas's lush arrangements of classic Chinese pop tunes from the 1930s, with a distinctly bluesy feel. It received positive international reviews from ''Rolling Stone'' to ''The Wall Street Journal'' to the ''Hong Kong Music Weekly''. It was #1 on the World Music Charts in Canada and garnered international attention, England's ''[[Q magazine|Q]]'' magazine awarding it 4 stars, and ''Mojo'' writing: \"It is simply gorgeous\". The album was chosen as one of the best discs of the year in France's ''[[Lib\u00e9ration]]'' newspaper. There was a lengthy profile for the album in ''The Wall Street Journal'', as well as an NPR interview. Lucas recently released an expanded concert version of ''The Edge of Heaven'' with his band, Gods and Monsters, and vocalists Sally Kwok and Mo Hai Jin, both from Shanghai.<ref name=\"garylucas.com\"/> The group received standing ovations at the [[Holland Festival]] in [[Amsterdam]] in June 2011.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lucas|first=Gary|title=Edge of Heaven Webpage|url=http://garylucas.com/epk/|website=Garylucas.com|accessdate=2012-05-06}}</ref>\n\n2016 saw the release of 3 new releases to positive critical response. ''Fleischerei: Music from Max Fleischer Cartoons'', featuring Joe Fiedler, Jeff Lederer, Michael Bates, Rob Garcia, and Sarah Stiles, was named \"One of the Best Albums of 2016\" by [[Down Beat]]<ref>http://garylucas.com/www/rvw/downbeat1612.jpg</ref> and \"One of the Best Indie Albums of 2016\" by [[Goldmine (magazine)]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.goldminemag.com/blogs/spin-cycle-blogs/spin-cycles-twelve-days-christmas-2016 |title = Spin Cycle's Twelve Days of Christmas, 2016|date = 2016-12-07}}</ref> ''Pearly Clouds'',<ref name=\"pearlyclouds.com\"/> an exploration of traditional Hungarian folk music, featuring saxophonist Toni Dezso and vocalist Eniko Szabo, was called \"a record of spiritual longing and timeless musical transcendence\" by [[FRoots]] and described as \"unusual and compelling listening\" by [[BBC Three]]. The acoustic folk pop collaboration with [[Jann Klose]], ''Stereopticon'' was given four stars by [[Mojo (magazine)]]. [[No Depression (magazine)]] wrote of the record, saying \"the harmonies, vocal interactions, and clear precise acoustic guitar provide the listener with enchanting listening.\u201d<ref>[http://www.lucasklose.com] {{dead link|date=January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Selected discography==\n* ''[[Skeleton at the Feast]]'' (1991)\n* ''[[Gods and Monsters (Gary Lucas album)|Gods and Monsters]]'' (1992)\n* ''[[Bad Boys of the Arctic]]'' (1994)\n* ''[[Pra\u017esk\u00e1 Stra\u0161idla (The Ghosts of Prague)]]'' with [[Urfaust]] (1996)\n* ''[[Evangeline (Gary Lucas album)|Evangeline]]'' (1997)\n* ''[[Busy Being Born]]'' (1998)\n* ''[[@ Paradiso]]'' (1999)\n* ''The Du-Tels \u2013 No Knowledge of Music Required'' with [[Peter Stampfel]] (2000)\n* ''[[Street of Lost Brothers]]'' (2000)\n* '' Level the Playing Field: Early HurlyBurly 1988\u20131994 '' (2000)\n* '' The Edge of Heaven (album)|The Edge of Heaven ''(2001)\n* ''[[Songs to No One 1991\u20131992]]'' with [[Jeff Buckley]] (2002)\n* '' Operators Are Standing By: The Essential Gary Lucas 1989-1996 '' (2003)\n* '' Diplopia '' (2003), with [[Jozef van Wissem]]\n* ''The Universe of Absence'' (2004) with Jozef van Wissem\n* ''Fast 'N' Bulbous \u2013 Pork Chop Blue Around the Rind'' (2005)\n* ''Coming Clean'' (2006)\n* ''Musical Blazeup'' (2007) with DJ Cosmo\n* ''Beyond the Pale'' (2008) with [[The Dark Poets]]\n* ''Chase the Devil'' (2008) with [[Dean Bowman]]\n* ''Rock the Joint'' (2008)  with [[Beardyman]]\n* ''Down the Rabbit Hole'' with [[Gerald Zbindin]] (2008)\n* ''Purple Somersault'' (2008) with DJ Cosmo\n* ''Fast 'n' Bulbous \u2013 Waxed Oop'' (2009)\n* ''Rishte'' [[Najma Akhtar]] & Gary Lucas (2009)\n* ''Music for the Eden Project''l single (2010)\n* '' The Ordeal of Civility '' (2011), released UK and Europe (2012)<ref name=\"Songwriter With Global Guitar\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/05/10/arts/music/gary-lucas-has-a-new-cd-the-ordeal-of-civility.html?_r=1&adxnnl=1&pagewanted=all&adxnnlx=1336812034-NRSQoxcvBMQwElVihb9i1g |author=Larry Richter |title=Songwriter With a Global Guitar |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=2014-07-11}}</ref>\n* ''Gary Lucas Plays Bohemian Classics,'' Czech Republic, (2012)\n* ''Popular Science'' with [[M'Lumbo]],  (Pursuance, 2013)\n* ''Cinefantastique'',  (Northern Spy, 2013)\n* ''[[Other World (album)|Other World]]'' with [[Peter Hammill]] (Esoteric Antenna, 2014)\n* ''Fleischerei'' (Cuneiform, 2016)<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n* ''Pearly Clouds'' (Trapeze, 2016)\n* ''Stereopticon'' with Jann Klose (Cosmic Trigger, 2016)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://garylucas.com/www/disc/ |title=Official Website |website=Garylucas.com |date= |accessdate=2015-11-04}}</ref>\n* ''The World of Captain Beefheart'' (Knitting Factory Records, 2017)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.garylucas.com/ Official website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070202124508/http://www.beefheart.com/datharp/albums/mbmembers/lucas.htm Lucas' biography and discography, on Captain Beefheart's \"band members\" section]\n* [https://www.nytimes.com/2011/05/10/arts/music/gary-lucas-has-a-new-cd-the-ordeal-of-civility.html?_r=1&pagewanted=all \"Songwriter with a Global Guitar\"] ''NY Times'' Review\n* {{YouTube|T-KS8p1vL_s|Edge of Heaven clip}}\n{{Gary Lucas|state=autocollapse}}\n{{Captain Beefheart}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lucas, Gary}}\n[[Category:Northern Spy Records artists]]\n[[Category:American blues guitarists]]\n[[Category:American male guitarists]]\n[[Category:American rock guitarists]]\n[[Category:Songwriters from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Syracuse, New York]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:Tzadik Records artists]]\n[[Category:The Magic Band members]]\n[[Category:Enemy Records artists]]\n[[Category:Guitarists from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:20th-century American guitarists]]